<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no" ?>
<FinalDraft DocumentType="Script" Template="No" Version="6">

  <DocumentRef DateTime="20260406T200428" id="d85cd055-00bf-439b-8a05-b767ab99a037">
    <XRef DateTime="20260222T010105" id="a7ca2c80-0c55-4d64-aa4b-18bd8a2c69bf"/>
    <XRef DateTime="20260222T010807" id="cef447fc-5244-4d84-8378-770e72544dca"/>
    <XRef DateTime="20260223T050521" id="76b240a0-8d50-4ae9-a87f-5b8199c0da70"/>
    <XRef DateTime="20260226T172657" id="04154a25-74da-41d3-a471-050e355222cb"/>
  </DocumentRef>

  <Content>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition" id="8e804054-1af4-45ec-b49a-2d77556aa048">
      <Text>COLD OPEN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8c5397ac-24f8-4492-80a7-7d9a409ddc2d">
      <Text>BLACK SCREEN.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="cc269d56-3465-4bfe-ba43-ad274abee475">
      <Text>Dripping. A pipe. Leaking onto something that stopped absorbing it a long time ago.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f6735973-58c9-4eb4-95cc-9daa2cd64402">
      <Text>Then— BREATHING. Shallow. Labored.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="651965f1-b346-47c3-ba99-f8ddb1898171">
      <Text>BOOM. BOOM. BOOM.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7c250a53-cdbc-4911-bd68-b54379ee8163">
      <Text>A pounding on a door rattling in its frame.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="aa410d7d-1c17-44a1-b6c4-8cd5157f3b33">
      <SceneProperties Length="4 6/8" Page="1" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HUNTER">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAZ">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. HUNTER'S APARTMENT - ST. MARKS PLACE - MORNING</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f7da832f-9c9f-4488-ac4b-d9daed7b5a4a">
      <Text>A basement unit. Half below street level. The kind of place landlords list as "garden apartment" because there's a window near the ceiling that technically faces sidewalk.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="df414fe3-cb26-4760-907b-19ca05046ded">
      <Text>One room. Maybe two hundred square feet. A shower head mounted directly over the toilet in the corner, shower curtain long gone, old water stain spreads from the corner. One suit, still in the dry cleaner plastic hangs from the shower head.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1546b770-e28a-4f26-b4e2-a17fa9fb6e0d">
      <Text>The FUTON dominates center of the room like a crime scene exhibit. No sheets. Mattress pad the color of regret. Comforter twisted into a shape that suggests the sleeper fought it and lost.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f0ab677d-8981-42cc-bb97-dd8e5c4221de">
      <Text>On this futon, shirtless, in boxer briefs that have seen better administrations, lies HUNTER REID (30s).</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5fe2e261-69b1-414c-bd04-1aa6bc733bda">
      <Text>He is not well. Definitely much less put together than he appeared at the poker game 3 hours ago.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="50065061-4fe4-470a-8a40-988567eb42ac">
      <Text>One arm dangles off the edge, fingers curled around nothing— the ghost of a bottle that rolled away in the night. His hair is matted to one side of his skull like he was licked by a large animal.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="373851d4-63a0-4ed8-82a3-ba278223eb59">
      <Text>BOOM. BOOM. BOOM.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="273de1c0-46b2-4fbc-a427-f0f55ad23a74">
      <Text>Hunter's eyes do not open.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="dd9f881b-35d0-4a60-95b5-1230fe04f8af">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="2783a3df-bf45-4d14-88e3-3f531060c990">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">Nnnnno</Text>
      <Text>. No. No no no.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a3991ed5-ef28-4786-8746-4150f9c10a63">
      <Text>BOOM. BOOM.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="feb616af-e407-4b21-a31c-5154f2958b5a">
      <Text>A tower of takeout containers— last night's pad </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">thai</Text>
      <Text> down to a weeks old Halal Guys at the base— wobbles. Falls. Styrofoam and soy sauce packets scatter like refugees.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="df0081a0-393a-4c48-9ff9-b5065cc94432">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="47f3437a-1a35-4804-bc5c-6cb6c3585038">
      <Text>(to the ceiling, to God)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="c34f662c-ef36-4ce3-b011-578947d00f89">
      <Text>Please.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7edd0715-36b4-4fb0-99f9-0184d0a48a0a">
      <Text>BOOM. BOOM. BOOM. BOOM.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="54715634-3902-4705-9e7d-696863959135">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="1905cffc-371c-4fc8-bcd6-10e2c26afb64">
      <Text>OKAY. OKAY. FUCK.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9f024a8f-b9eb-4578-8ce7-c2ac8d8235bc">
      <Text>He sits up. Mistake.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="652e969c-34da-4520-9319-f4eb1244b8a9">
      <Text>The room tilts. His stomach sends an urgent memo: we are going to vomit. The question is when, not if. He presses both palms into his eyes. Breathes. The nausea crests, holds, and— by the slimmest of margins— retreats.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="39f418e5-d5ce-4b8a-95d5-8ec3f37ade69">
      <Text>Not gone. Just waiting.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ce0cdb9b-e656-40a9-8904-fa1b11bac2d8">
      <Text>He surveys the room. THE ROOM:</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="cfdf13fe-f18c-489c-805d-b1511392919a">
      <Text>A hot plate on a mini-fridge on plywood on milk crates. A jar of Folgers instant coffee, lid off, powder spilled across the surface. A dirty mug— Columbia Law logo, the "L" in "Law" chipped off so it reads "Columbia Aw."</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="01b656c3-25ac-43ac-90d8-9adfe94833ab">
      <Text>A folding card table with a laptop that has a crack across the screen in the shape of a fist. Yellow legal pads in stacks that were once organized and have since surrendered. Law books everywhere— not on shelves, there are no shelves— on the floor, in stacks, some serving as furniture.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9bb40064-c8cf-4f1c-9160-3f502554f760">
      <Text>Empty Jameson bottles. Just... part of the landscape.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f045d7be-babe-4611-be4c-653fdd2b4a7a">
      <Text>BOOM. BOOM. BOOM. BOOM. BOOM.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="9509bb8f-0b36-4700-a4f6-a8b93869c959">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="4da71835-fc63-4c93-b4a9-ac184aac5449">
      <Text>Fine. Fine. FUCK! Fine fine.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3535710f-6243-4d5d-956e-5359e2f0b857">
      <Text>He stands. Shuffles six feet to the door in his boxer briefs, hunched, one hand on his stomach.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="0ab026bc-4339-43a2-b3c8-8fb69d070a9d">
      <Text>He undoes the chain. Turns the deadbolt. Slides the bar lock. Pulls.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="31f4678b-8b45-4853-b11b-b49a3d8fa469">
      <Text>The hallway light slices into his retinas.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ff7d9149-423d-42e8-9429-1de64622e114">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="af779fa7-e594-4be9-9a26-cac6aadbf8c2">
      <Text>(squinting, recoiling)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="7714bb12-8634-4cbd-ab99-ae045b443a4a">
      <Text>Jesus Christ—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="134ce382-e13f-4afa-b2bd-ffb4185a5565">
      <Text>JAZ.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="09296d58-8fc4-466b-9cef-eabecc9eb964">
      <Text>Still in Tanner's suit jacket over the harness. Combat boots. Shaved skull. Messenger bag.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8b4e99be-e51f-4b2c-bdb3-6b2bd2481190">
      <Text>Her eyes are red. Not from crying— from refusing to.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="708d6847-e448-45c4-9297-84f9bcf8e631">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="3c4f242d-4346-44aa-849d-f51c8ac3931a">
      <Text>(blinking)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="13daed6e-1262-46d8-a262-1dcface19bdb">
      <Text>Phoenix?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c8cd1727-f532-4ae9-9714-5efb27118ebb">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="5ab4694f-02ad-47a6-8dd3-1b253654a615">
      <Text>Let me in.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a017a138-2158-4ce9-8d76-86cde319ecb8">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="1e54eea2-ec85-4f46-ab94-fa04682af0bf">
      <Text>How do you know where I—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c8670d7e-3b8e-41e0-a34a-960d27aa2e5d">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e5195486-bcf6-47fb-b704-9e7cd05f5c2f">
      <Text>You gave Skyler your address last month when you were drunk. Skyler told everyone. Let me in.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="d05bac5f-eb8e-4642-8dd2-ca86038be538">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="aca811a0-da74-43b5-b0ef-20e6e464018f">
      <Text>You already cleaned me out last night-</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2924e217-a820-4b9e-a234-bbbc49998c86">
      <Text>A wad of hundreds land on the floor at his feet.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4532da7d-5b40-419b-a7e7-7a3bc25c25d8">
      <Text>He steps back. She enters. Takes in the room in one scan. The futon. The hot plate. The bottles. The coffee powder. The graduation photo holding a diploma smiling at its own future.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1f13b455-1723-478d-b5e8-42cea3ea3040">
      <Text>Doesn't comment. This isn't the worst room she's been in. It just might be the saddest.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="cb6d6559-cfb9-4391-8926-7ca8b8b5d87a">
      <Text>She drops the messenger bag on the futon. And settles on the cleanest spot she can find, the floor.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9c29f48f-0c02-43fe-a58a-d5eb7939ed48">
      <Text>Hunter crosses his arms. An attempt at authority from a man who has none. Trying to not lunge at the wad of cash, playing as cool as he can with no cool.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4327edd9-d72e-4bea-ae54-5b1c055e322b">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="614d2d5f-5fd6-419d-85ca-b939fb4ed16b">
      <Text>Okay. So. This is... What?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="862d7428-b205-4e82-a517-a0ccf5c93756">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="c94f6745-97f2-4c83-bee5-083927ec0ff5">
      <Text>I need a lawyer.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ab351ce1-1e6f-4258-bbcf-b208295f3d21">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="deef7d29-e331-4a77-800a-5365c9a14e87">
      <Text>(looking at the room, at himself, at his life)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="0561e634-7901-4293-bd2e-e8fbed07ff67">
      <Text>What happened.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="40cb0575-8810-41fa-b787-9a69665bfa00">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="df546715-77cc-43bc-a7dd-7c665f915701">
      <Text>My mother got arrested. This morning. I don't— </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="a09f3027-d914-4969-ae71-90ff4711c2a6">
      <Text>(she is actually shaken for the first time)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="4ce27004-526b-4455-b348-fbca7af8620f">
      <Text>They put her in a car in handcuffs. And my brother. He's fourteen. Some woman with a clipboard put him in a van.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f92b9210-758a-45c6-96c1-e46a28cf94ee">
      <Text>She pull a pack of smokes from her bag, shakes one out. Hunter absentmindedly pads himself where a breast pocket would have been. She tosses his the pack.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="e3992d0f-be34-479c-9716-89101c060108">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="1f3ea16b-297e-4c69-abfe-bd387061cbfb">
      <Text>(he lights his smoke on the hotplate)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="964babc2-37f1-4971-8ba5-798718e50272">
      <Text>Okay. Slow down. Start from—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="69409b8f-f2d0-4e57-a5cb-abd1a3742a92">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="da6695be-4f52-45cb-b2a4-39c951ed85bf">
      <Text>I came home and there were cops everywhere. They said everything is seized.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="67955212-4081-485c-84dc-3e214bd6a0f4">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="6870e8a2-4b70-4cae-8c4f-bf10c7418068">
      <Text>My clothes are in there. everything.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f224edaa-978d-4970-be8f-0bea8d8b1154">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="0de4b377-ae04-499a-b42b-ee0e9685aac1">
      <Text>(uncertain)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="83558401-071e-43c6-9175-18871b6e15e7">
      <Text>What about your dad? He's um... still in the picture?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="700fc5c8-afca-4289-b1e1-fc12bbbee185">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f0c08414-a57d-4c5f-bfb1-17e3551b3f77">
      <Text>Yes. I've been calling him. Straight to voicemail.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a17a88a2-6a82-4541-9eed-8ca814c36105">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="9f8cefd0-b6f5-4849-95c4-8b8161c12fd5">
      <Text>Okay. And what did the cops tell you about the charges?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4bf3839a-2041-4bd0-a8dc-047469be154b">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="9d3c6bc5-a542-4c05-8171-8c16c6b372d7">
      <Text>They told me my mom was being taken to Central Booking. That's all I know. That's everything. I need to get my brother back.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="72339853-2de1-42a2-b19c-09e6b4ec29df">
      <Text>The Jameson fog is fighting with the adrenaline, and the adrenaline is winning. His eyes are doing the thing— the sharpening. The thing she saw at the poker table.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="de6b26aa-0ec2-40ed-a0da-14705b5ba83f">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="5137126d-f753-402d-b6af-241c5e73aeeb">
      <Text>Your dad. What's his name?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="798d4c63-4e28-41fd-9004-f6075afca565">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="2583dbc8-2e06-447d-a32d-381fbe3515a1">
      <Text>Kevin McCort.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f62c5d8b-a463-4c5e-9909-ddb88afede5d">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="a8addcd3-cc29-43e0-9794-c169d30f92a2">
      <Text>(shocked)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="119ce295-a47a-443a-8963-2827f36cf1a6">
      <Text>Oh! Um... The MedAnalytic guy, right?.. Kevin McCort.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="3695681c-5e51-47ec-ad53-0161720c90cd">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="1e8b23aa-039b-4a6c-8223-27dcd33fcc1c">
      <Text>Yes.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="e3ec5033-5686-4304-ba3c-7bcdaaeb580a">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e9eb85be-7138-4992-990e-bda974975adc">
      <Text>Shit.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e5f416c5-0ddc-4437-bd83-bfbb99c2898d">
      <Text>He turns to the "kitchen." Dumps Folgers into the Columbia Aw mug. Runs the tap. The water is brown for three seconds. Goes clear. Mostly. He fills the mug. Drinks the cold instant coffee in two gulps. His face contorts. The vomit memo returns. He overrules it.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4a16176a-c68e-4e57-9678-e3da0e69818a">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="5fd9ca72-442a-4943-9e3f-1825448b293a">
      <Text>(swallowing, wiping his mouth)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="4204eab4-ea0d-4d22-952e-45ee7ce7c3c9">
      <Text>Okay. I know a guy.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1691ed92-5674-4d84-ba53-127d4f098b1c">
      <Text>He looks around the room. Locates an ANDROID PHONE. Old. A Samsung something, the model number worn off the back, a crack running diagonally across the lower corner of the screen. The kind of phone that receives everything and syncs to nothing.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="02d1121f-3cc8-4371-9750-e7c7c3cdc17c">
      <Text>NO SERVICE.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="800f6649-8e24-4088-9d77-6cabc2e01460">
      <Text>He stares at it. Taps it. Taps it again. Holds it up like he's searching for a signal that doesn't exist.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4e5b94fc-43de-4c96-8390-a1fbc821f247">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="89b57e0a-1d48-4952-b232-15ae48fdba48">
      <Text>Fuck.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a22a0b58-e9b0-46dc-857d-62bda159309d">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f530a13e-f6ab-44bd-986f-1416cf1f8aff">
      <Text>What?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="bb46a6bc-6517-4ddd-b164-9ff6b400cd26">
      <Text>He has the specific look of shame of a man confessing something small that reveals something enormous.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="45beae92-acf9-4fba-8732-e209f48beb93">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="5bbb4910-b962-4c9e-b77a-acba9f3f8225">
      <Text>I'm out of minutes.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4c662518-cc39-4c7b-ab8b-1ca1948a8093">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b716f2dd-3376-476a-92eb-1cdc274e75e1">
      <Text>You're out of minutes.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="0413e6b7-c6ff-4697-8106-604ca68aa0c6">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="3ea7bd60-6863-43da-bb23-cdd86c3ce06f">
      <Text>It's a prepaid.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition" id="3326b620-9cef-425e-af74-7da1e7d3d97d">
      <Text>SMASH CUT TO:</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="76b33710-ac32-47c4-9a93-49cb0c71c41d">
      <Text>TITLE CARD: THE PLAYBOY</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="493e8e16-4dae-4a3f-bdf4-30fefb3c2d22">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 6/8" Page="6" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BOOKING OFFICER">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CORRECTIONS OFFICER">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DUI GUY">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEVIN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. CENTRAL BOOKING - 100 CENTRE STREET - MORNING</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2e38b7e4-1227-4b72-b229-d92296b0c7ab">
      <Text>Fluorescent hell. Everything is the color of nothing— beige walls, beige floor, beige despair.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ccb6ada2-6751-4ffc-846b-0d73d4fc202a">
      <Text>KEVIN McCORT, still in his $4,000 suit, sits on a metal bench in a holding area. His hands are cuffed in front of him. The </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">Patek</Text>
      <Text> scratched from the rough arrest.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d9c5dd88-ef39-42df-9676-1f23dc47413c">
      <Text>His hair is wrong for the first time in his adult life.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="fecedc73-58c5-44f3-886c-be8eb23c2b3d">
      <Text>Around him: the morning's intake. A </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">DUI</Text>
      <Text>. Two assaults. A man who appears to be sleeping standing up. The democracy of the holding cell— everyone equal, everyone waiting, everyone smelling like the same combination of fear and municipal disinfectant.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ef1c575a-0c45-49a3-b2f5-566a79e3ef77">
      <Text>Kevin is staring straight ahead. The look of a man who is still waiting for someone to realize this is a mistake.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a237040d-61f2-45eb-a2bc-3389f2a6944f">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="7a1e2845-9499-477c-9e13-d392e7451dc4">
      <Text>(to the BOOKING OFFICER behind the desk)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="ec1a8415-d49b-4c13-bc35-36ba62e950a7">
      <Text>I still need to make a phone call.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="331e4ce2-309d-43bd-a088-30bbc79382ec">
      <Text>BOOKING OFFICER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="b332e326-bf01-4158-8f4f-6f8e3e3ecc30">
      <Text>(not looking up)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="bf9d53a9-2850-445d-bb29-67a8c5a10a84">
      <Text>Again, when we're done processing.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="52c5fa33-3646-4ff4-b4af-b6f9b98c1b6d">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="68ef8c68-8aab-410c-97ac-93a493645cb6">
      <Text>I've been sitting here for forty minutes. My attorney—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="40681bd1-e1b1-48e1-9823-1228692d83d6">
      <Text>BOOKING OFFICER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f45d43a1-da73-4d0e-b2a0-d924d31642cb">
      <Text>When. We're done. Processing.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="29d8cb7e-229e-4350-a9b6-6d98a74f7aec">
      <Text>Kevin's jaw works. The COO voice— impresses no one here.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d7a80343-0632-4f6e-ab7c-2522d1192716">
      <Text>The man next to him on the bench— </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">DUI</Text>
      <Text>, bloodshot eyes, vomit on his shoe— leans over.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="46040409-6a75-4147-ae1e-f3397f6387e3">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">DUI</Text>
      <Text> GUY</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="e981e254-9e04-4ef0-8d29-8ddbe7d5ed8b">
      <Text>(conversational)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="71ad6c25-021e-4cc7-8d76-b32cccdc2e7a">
      <Text>First time?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="af981a9d-edb7-4d4a-8d31-4a379c2ea099">
      <Text>Kevin doesn't answer.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="617735de-5dd2-4b0b-b153-430e5bc271dd">
      <Text>A CORRECTIONS OFFICER approaches with a clipboard.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4313fa96-3b07-4564-b078-d6faef1e0795">
      <Text>CORRECTIONS OFFICER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="daaedc38-2a1d-43a7-b921-850db72a80b9">
      <Text>McCort, Kevin. Step up.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="091f7db6-81df-48f8-8ef0-28f2a2e332ab">
      <Text>Kevin stands. Smooths his suit. A reflex. Muscle memory from a different world.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="616b7f01-f9e0-491d-b05b-c471114b4aac">
      <Text>CORRECTIONS OFFICER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="cb344caa-b87e-42a8-b169-78fe8b1b537f">
      <Text>Personal effects.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5ed8bded-6470-44bb-a135-ad5bab5ccc7d">
      <Text>Kevin empties his pockets onto the counter. Wallet. AirPods</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="General" id="5729f83a-1d9f-4c7b-b9d2-7c99320da1e0">
      <Text>case. A business card holder, silver, engraved. Keys to a</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="General" id="392cf63e-302f-42bd-8d8e-c1e701263ba1">
      <Text>townhouse he'll learn has been seized.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="758e23a0-154b-4b68-8fdf-f6466f479ce3">
      <Text>CORRECTIONS OFFICER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="46ed2abf-0bc8-40f3-a107-e1fc0e3eb2d3">
      <Text>Wedding ring. The watch.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e52c5e43-dbf5-4945-9989-9ece769383ce">
      <Text>Kevin looks at his hand. At his wrist.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c5450105-5d1f-491d-9578-74a7646db5f0">
      <Text>CORRECTIONS OFFICER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="3b6858d0-5e88-4b81-aff1-694ad9078fbc">
      <Text>All jewelry. Policy.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d8518341-3a4c-4029-97d2-a531bef10d3e">
      <Text>He pulls them off. Sets them on the counter. The sound they makes on the metal tray is very small and very final.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="2ebdb4d8-f523-4c0a-90f6-d6053b88496a">
      <Text>CORRECTIONS OFFICER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="4dd40032-eb61-4f74-8007-c7ca8dbee6eb">
      <Text>Face the camera.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f679e949-9843-4492-b463-2b90a1894111">
      <Text>Kevin turns. The mugshot camera. Industrial. Merciless.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="General" id="ec46ae65-9f23-424d-a46b-63867bdad8e4">
      <Text>The light is designed to make everyone look guilty.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="6e1c0766-3c95-4135-8cc7-24832d6dcf6a">
      <Text>CORRECTIONS OFFICER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="c60d5a32-7ce0-456c-80b4-2875b24d0861">
      <Text>Hold the card.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="82327032-5436-4a7f-812f-2ab761bf928b">
      <Text>A booking card with his name and a number. Kevin McCort.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="General" id="a00fd2c1-69c7-4d3b-92ce-1823b8373982">
      <Text>Just another number in a system that processes sixty</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="General" id="a0bb4e2b-118d-408c-8e7a-f8ac26c1f596">
      <Text>thousand arrests a year and remembers none of them.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4003e9d2-1c3f-4364-b0b8-3f6c983f92cd">
      <Text>He holds it. The camera flashes.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f45f812b-0c76-4934-8bf6-3f0391a27adb">
      <Text>KEVIN McCORT. COO. Princeton. </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">Patek</Text>
      <Text> Nautilus. </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">Caymus</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="General" id="72109a2e-6159-46e0-8fda-9493870ceeda">
      <Text>Cabernet. Corner office. Doorman building. Family dinner</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="General" id="0d075c58-5dab-4cda-96b3-38609cb270cf">
      <Text>every night at six.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="0615796a-22c0-4b96-a74e-1d8bf4e02fe0">
      <Text>Inmate.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="5a435edc-b7b2-463c-b151-49bbb3141014">
      <SceneProperties Length="3 2/8" Page="7" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CNBC ANCHOR">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HUNTER">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAZ">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. HUNTER'S APARTMENT - ST. MARKS PLACE - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="bdad7086-8230-48fb-b00f-5ea1f4f796d7">
      <Text>He puts Jaz's phone on speaker. Sets it back on the counter.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="df127b77-43be-4cec-bac2-4e01d1d4aff9">
      <Text>Hold music. Tinny. Terrible.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a14183b8-328b-42b4-afd5-b8c0acba17c3">
      <Text>Jaz stares at the phone. Hunter stares at the ceiling, stretching his back.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4d73b23a-b895-44ef-8c88-3882d083fcb6">
      <Text>The dripping pipe marks time.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="af6cfaf8-0f87-4f6a-aea7-c960fe0b841d">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="44d88a5b-1cb9-4a76-b03a-19bd663311d4">
      <Text>(quiet)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="4d30bc10-daba-48ff-b852-181fda2d8b85">
      <Text>I should have been there for Jamie.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="46b6f4a9-8a26-44c6-b2f9-af090636786b">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="eb340e2c-79bd-40c2-8aa0-437519dad1ea">
      <Text>Who?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="dc1834c5-ff1d-4dd1-a684-0c8b8261d5e0">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="daa4903b-240e-4cd9-8d59-a9f8d11d240c">
      <Text>(racked with guilt)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="71fcbe71-2291-4e25-8c21-2ce0aa16f691">
      <Text>My little brother. If I was there they wouldn't have taken him.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d1117f0d-184d-4e8a-bad9-0af10394f1f5">
      <Text>Hunter looks at her. Whatever he's about to say, he thinks better of it.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7dd18704-ca53-43e5-8e99-a8d2c152d8fe">
      <Text>The hold music continues.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="7144c9d9-2214-408d-9f02-bfa8ed31a47d">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="8d6c0b96-d53e-409c-8c5f-c8f31bf5b808">
      <Text>You have coffee powder on your nipple, by the way.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c7929185-d6bc-4fd7-a91a-184c1e786749">
      <Text>Hunter looks down. An unmistakable smear of Folgers instant. On his nipple. He has no explanation for how it got there. He brushes at it. It doesn't help.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="3dcbc1cd-21bb-4d44-83d0-457f2d8cfe02">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="6ea1d618-50a4-4a69-9239-c55da42be59e">
      <Text>Yeah. I don't— that's not—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="f7ffffb4-26ae-45a2-b036-8372f4dc20cc">
      <Text>(gives up)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="adad1f77-a801-4c5e-aef2-68c84ad44103">
      <Text>It's been a morning.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d6afb6d9-35ee-4b7f-8625-d37c0af0f5d1">
      <Text>The hold music cuts out.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="54ce06c4-e08b-46bd-9090-39447f784716">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="55e8eb47-6381-4660-922b-852952a8a26a">
      <Text>(scoops it up, urgent)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="1825157c-1dd6-4e96-a300-9bd057add0b8">
      <Text>Danny. Yeah. I'm here. What do you—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="25258ddd-984f-402c-bb6f-5c654cc9580a">
      <Text>He listens. His expression changes. Hardens. The drunk evaporates. What's left is something leaner.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="de600f61-20f5-4eca-b83e-24d3134f5dd3">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b6c5a6f3-af3a-48c5-9b59-7f59ceea7e0a">
      <Text>Both of them. On the same warrant.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="e965851a-6daf-417d-83fe-c031d2416b4f">
      <Text>(listening)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="7e64deb5-0937-4d93-b1c7-44fd8deae973">
      <Text>Martin Act. Okay. Securities fraud. Grand larceny— how much are we—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="22954924-70a4-42ee-8fc9-399deb20d5c1">
      <Text>(listening)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="be9e203f-eca4-4691-977c-b4b8307af1ce">
      <Text>Jesus.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="a060bb4e-0fcd-4932-b410-6da54201e8e9">
      <Text>(listening)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="84ff645a-47fa-4684-8fea-a73978a2e0b6">
      <Text>And the wife? What are they—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="9c6f1413-bd59-482f-9ef2-42c9f6914f85">
      <Text>(listening)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="fe6ae690-27f3-40a0-96b5-21d8ed7b6913">
      <Text>Just conspiracy? Okay. Is she—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="6e7edd66-02a6-48a7-8f8a-102d21a94593">
      <Text>(listening)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="12e2522a-c4da-4f2b-821f-f742540d83b6">
      <Text>She's already at 100 Centre. Okay. Danny, one more thing. Kevin McCort. Where was he picked up.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="b6433b30-7b30-48f7-a8b8-e343299e143f">
      <Text>(listening)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="2fb202dd-87b1-40c4-943a-3664f6dd4bcb">
      <Text>His office. This morning. So he's—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="57861b7c-8967-44aa-be85-b067931b1be4">
      <Text>(listening)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="324791c0-75d8-4a75-8bfd-763df559230f">
      <Text>He's there now. Okay. Danny. Thanks. Yeah, we're even now. Have a nice fucking life... and yes, you are still a piece of shit.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b5d861ea-6ae7-45af-b87a-9522f87a0d74">
      <Text>He hangs up. Stares at the phone for a long moment. Then he looks at Jaz.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f4520917-8f57-473d-a1dd-7e59a82f6ecd">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="1f469660-c99c-4f29-9be8-279cf9e2b063">
      <Text>Your dad was arrested this morning. Martin Act violations. Securities fraud. Wire fraud. Grand larceny. Money laundering. He's being processed at Central Booking now.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8d78d8e9-eb97-4b5f-bbe3-c338f473cb0c">
      <Text>Jaz doesn't move. Doesn't blink.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="777a66f9-ffa8-4132-a65d-89b3dc492a07">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="75b353ac-7451-4c5a-a00c-3cfd0b42ee05">
      <Text>Your mom's there too. She's been charged with conspiracy.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="107c0048-e9d5-44c7-a3b6-fc816490f483">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="b611ce6b-e05b-4ba2-963a-f7ccee36513b">
      <Text>(quiet)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="25ad4f26-a4c9-4947-999a-e6971fee3e8e">
      <Text>And Jamie.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4ae6f820-f792-4b66-9309-49a0e76345fb">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e7b682c3-c142-4afe-b860-7e37423b4441">
      <Text>ACS, is the most likely. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="0717ba9f-084b-4047-8615-f47e54f1d093">
      <Text>(off her look)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="348c6c00-88c5-4931-97eb-0c02b7669e0d">
      <Text>You're eighteen, you're a sibling— you can file for emergency kinship placement. But you need a residential address. And you need to look like—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7de18aa8-cc4f-4ec2-b033-ae37e90982dc">
      <Text>He gestures at her. The harness. The boots. The shaved tattooed skull.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a085aae5-9810-4482-81b7-31a0e69dc3c3">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="cc707df2-c6f0-4a1e-b910-2bcbfe1ba0f3">
      <Text>Like what.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="6f7bc8a3-68e2-4fdb-ae23-8e8a3b49eb5d">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="dd04a5a6-2f2b-46ae-a93c-9ee45998bfd9">
      <Text>Like someone a caseworker would give a kid to.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="52f18b7c-959c-449a-b16f-5d15dd08f888">
      <Text>She absorbs this. Everything. The weight of it stacking.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a456531f-a119-4ed3-bb15-1c92b54a8f8b">
      <Text>On the floor. In a basement.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c10535a7-e85a-4fe8-93fc-495dbb4b17ad">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="c1d5f22a-90e0-469f-a52c-583a8b068626">
      <Text>We have an address.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="63aa86e2-375c-4a77-a9ef-304fa1107f33">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="590ce031-5dba-4d6a-b551-0d55c773acd8">
      <Text>Um, yeah. One that has not been seized.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ebeae177-2710-4f2e-82eb-ec5f36360ff4">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="88a7dcf3-caf6-4d83-bfce-32ba3df19f4d">
      <Text>Okay. I'll use this one.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="eea00b43-5c01-4451-8ebf-5e6a2a9962cd">
      <Text>The phone buzzes. A NEWS ALERT. Hunter looks at it.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="8aa6bec2-c0b9-48b4-a376-ebe5dc13f1c4">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="ea4e6418-471c-4fa4-a3c2-97dfa47f0128">
      <Text>Yeah, maybe one that is a legal residence... not your lawyers, um... Office.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e5efd53e-39a6-4e1b-9ec2-e205f7e72f6d">
      <Text>He moves to the laptop. The cracked screen blinks to life.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="03708caa-2a94-47b1-9419-edc8d5768a57">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">CNBC</Text>
      <Text>. BREAKING NEWS banner. The chyron reads:</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="430a3ed5-7c3a-4af6-b603-81e9adfb79a8">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">MEDANALYTIC</Text>
      <Text> COO KEVIN McCORT ARRESTED ON SECURITIES FRAUD CHARGES — DEVELOPING</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="26a6032d-7576-4cd6-b3d9-bb1f682eb6fc">
      <Text>A shaky cell phone video. Kevin's face. Being hauled off the hood of his own town car. Coffee on the sidewalk. The </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">Patek</Text>
      <Text> catching morning light.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="d8d4f088-26bc-41b3-a830-0dda78396caf">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">CNBC</Text>
      <Text> ANCHOR (V.O.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="eb8f83eb-4b9a-4b6c-9548-38cf79a3b722">
      <Text>—sources confirming that Kevin McCort, Chief Operating Officer of MedAnalytic Systems, was taken into custody by NYPD detectives this morning outside the company's Midtown offices—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1ed6c150-669f-47dd-9d87-bc12745336c2">
      <Text>Jaz watches her father get arrested on a cracked laptop screen. Her face doesn't move. Hunter watches her watch it.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="83e723cd-5b1b-4173-af02-f83f8ba94c62">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">CNBC</Text>
      <Text> ANCHOR (V.O.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="570b63cd-b3c4-43e0-b060-b0d34cea971a">
      <Text>—the arrest comes just one day after MedAnalytic announced terms on its landmark acquisition of </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">Merkur</Text>
      <Text> BioData—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="bff8f47e-d4bc-4120-8f8a-f23bb4f5e5d2">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="1a4af3b8-8373-4176-8d40-59f33807914f">
      <Text>(quiet, still watching)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="8cc016b1-1e8f-43b8-b324-4dde0eb7cbb5">
      <Text>Turn it off.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="91ab6118-1fb5-48a1-8f8b-35d166540e18">
      <Text>Hunter closes the laptop.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="fa93a3b9-e873-41f2-b93f-f6e1535425a4">
      <Text>Silence. The pipe drips.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f7748976-f777-44a4-94ed-0b24f42d4e7b">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="2f086d78-7783-42d5-9fb2-a8235319ded9">
      <Text>How do I get my brother back.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4ae6f3f9-6e72-4057-87b1-8d77e4d75893">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="cdfbe7d6-102f-4875-a60c-7ff3aa73f743">
      <Text>First we need to get off this floor.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="cb94f90a-f517-48e6-9b02-a663f425bf40">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 2/8" Page="11" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="INTAKE OFFICER">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. CENTRAL BOOKING - WOMEN'S INTAKE - SAME TIME</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="0e40233a-ae56-4985-999b-5a882c37c2dc">
      <Text>Three floors below Kevin, a different line. Same fluorescent hell. Same beige.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c97687e9-097d-4e59-b735-97595957d9bb">
      <Text>JANET McCORT stands at the intake counter in Lululemon and bare feet. They took her shoes at processing— laces are a liability. Her toes are perfect. Pedicure: "Ballet Slipper" by Essie. $85 at the salon on Columbus.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="35b80589-72c5-451e-b8a1-3be1732fb4bb">
      <Text>She is the only woman in this line who smells like La Mer.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="af4f49b1-b2e5-49d1-9a7e-ba424ebd3185">
      <Text>Around her: a prostitution bust— four women, two still in platform heels, comparing bail stories. A woman in a hospital gown handcuffed to a wheelchair. A girl who can't be older than twenty, mascara down to her chin, shaking.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2a2fed21-00e6-4b96-a114-eabe5097cd92">
      <Text>Janet stands among them like a mannequin placed in the wrong store.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3c4aa6f5-5765-4bc9-896b-d7a57863b00c">
      <Text>Her hair is still in the messy bun. Still perfect. The one thing they can't inventory.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="9e8e82c4-8ea6-4d4e-9916-74500e1ddc33">
      <Text>INTAKE OFFICER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e40b4d85-8a6c-43d5-bbad-9d931a8eff72">
      <Text>McCort, Janet. Step forward.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6801e7de-761b-48e2-a37d-25e2e624d11f">
      <Text>She steps forward. Smooth. Controlled. The walk of a woman who has entered rooms her entire life with a perfect mask.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="d04809cc-b082-4a75-8e36-af07895a2b6b">
      <Text>INTAKE OFFICER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="2def1497-a290-46d4-b0c1-f1655d64a9ee">
      <Text>Personal effects.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="0ae4c60e-b03d-4a83-bd9b-25addf034bee">
      <Text>Janet places her items on the counter one at a time. Each one laid down with the precision of a place setting.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f2298195-2a78-4b55-9346-ef165050ed9e">
      <Text>Phone. Cartier Love bracelet. Van </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">Cleef</Text>
      <Text> earrings. Wedding ring— she removes it without hesitation, without ceremony. Sets it on the tray like it's a tip at a restaurant.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9c5fbb9c-6251-467b-9ea5-40dc4f0c485f">
      <Text>The intake officer watches her. Most women cry at this point. Or argue. Or freeze.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c0680b50-cfdf-441b-abe5-e82fb71d4962">
      <Text>Janet does none of these things.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="e2416cd8-1c3c-4465-9b24-df63989eb73c">
      <Text>INTAKE OFFICER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="3dd1b08c-29ff-4a5d-a54a-8f87ac1acd2b">
      <Text>Face the camera.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="311c1ae0-539c-4b5f-b110-429940f4c9f4">
      <Text>Janet turns. Finds the lens. And does something no one in this room expects.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9dcb3e9b-0ddf-4253-b750-2e46ed753502">
      <Text>She squares her shoulders. Lifts her chin. Sets her jaw at the exact angle that she's spent twenty years calibrating in mirrors and bathroom selfies and reflections in restaurant windows.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7bf653dd-af16-45da-bba0-9935f12366f4">
      <Text>The camera flashes.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f470c33c-86e8-4cab-83a9-f06226273375">
      <Text>It is, by any technical measure, a perfect fashion mugshot.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="cca3b3eb-6e24-4d0b-bc4b-9c731d698863">
      <Text>INTAKE OFFICER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="bfc92226-b57c-4f28-92ba-347c755bc0df">
      <Text>(a beat, thrown)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a7cfce08-fab2-4e2c-9346-09aa583ff8bd">
      <Text>Turn left.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1c60730f-2a34-4928-aca7-da685a4ff3b1">
      <Text>She turns. The profile is equally composed.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b96cab4a-3366-4bf3-a787-eaeb537c5c3d">
      <Text>Flash.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="75a7fc1c-3742-4ae9-8759-5efae3e6b716">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 2/8" Page="12" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHUCKLES">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="INTERCOM">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAZ">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. ALPHABET CITY - AVENUE D - MORNING</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="03ff00af-4bfb-4853-a998-4259fcdf7647">
      <Text>The part of the Lower East Side that the real estate agents would describe as combat </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">sheek</Text>
      <Text>. A door with no handle next to a sign that reads MASSAGE in a font that promises no massage.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="42f6c624-c6d0-4a6f-80fa-62d022654df8">
      <Text>JAZ walks with purpose. She's scrolling Discord— an old group chat for show bookings, mostly dead. Seven months back: Chuckles posted a flyer for a gig at some warehouse, with a photo of himself holding it on his stoop. "come thru 214 D unit 5 if u need tix." The man doxxed himself to sell $8 tickets to a show twelve people attended.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2d7bae02-f4a1-4aae-915f-0ecdb4b03e78">
      <Text>She stops. Looks up.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6e657c10-b5f8-4374-a7a5-9aee59d10ccb">
      <Text>THE BUILDING: a five-story tenement that was old when punk was young. The fire escape is rust holding hands with more rust. A window on the second floor is covered in tinfoil. The front door has a buzzer panel with eight units—half the labels scratched off, one replaced with duct tape that reads "CHUCK" in Sharpie.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e8babaad-05c5-4393-8bd1-f94f73488f97">
      <Text>It's not good. But it's a legal address.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e25b2048-7bbd-4085-952d-496ba8cccf54">
      <Text>She buzzes unit 5.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ebb6b791-ee84-4ed4-9c6b-09f1fb469e57">
      <Text>Nothing.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d2014990-1082-46d9-a069-76e78214f222">
      <Text>Again. Holds it.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d0d574c1-eaaf-4db6-8106-918ec770d90d">
      <Text>Nothing.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e3894fc2-4676-47a5-8a93-06d36cde74bd">
      <Text>She holds the buzzer down for ten seconds. Somewhere inside, something electronic screams.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="8ac73abe-9d93-415b-a30e-65669a12f07f">
      <Text>INTERCOM</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="1a6553eb-e21a-45ea-91ee-efbfbbb952e0">
      <Text>(distorted, a voice from the bottom of a well)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b7e02ef3-180f-44ec-8da4-997aeb719f38">
      <Text>WHAT. WHAT. FUCKING WHAT.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="00a1ce74-c20e-472a-b28b-82b82562aa97">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="54643fdd-92b3-4548-aeb0-ce49d47bba22">
      <Text>Chuckles. It's Phoenix.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="af32c9d5-f9fe-489f-8a79-51dfd0ce2908">
      <Text>Static. A long beat.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="22f71ee9-6e1d-4577-b806-b0feb11566e6">
      <Text>CHUCKLES (INTERCOM)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f3ace149-0734-45f7-a286-d1f70534e688">
      <Text>...Phoenix?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="abb86fd7-1a9f-490a-b62c-81522bb852d7">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="63e4a4dc-40aa-469f-91d4-55dc82280575">
      <Text>Buzz me in.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="700a5529-b375-4635-b689-ad79e4d4065f">
      <Text>CHUCKLES (INTERCOM)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="de2877e1-1656-4770-895e-5d1b4271a78e">
      <Text>It's like... what time is—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="6a61d758-b133-4491-ba54-93179d41c8c9">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b588b18e-8eb7-4a61-9790-b22bfae27f9e">
      <Text>Now, Chuckles.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8be11e69-6fb6-4133-af83-442b292e1a79">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">BZZZZZZZ</Text>
      <Text>.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7af1030c-0137-44c6-b1e6-37cee22f3de0">
      <Text>She pushes through the door.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="1807ad0d-5073-4e71-82fd-a4abe6c44e8b">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 2/8" Page="13" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ACS ADMIN #1">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ACS ADMIN #2">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. ACS MANHATTAN FIELD OFFICE - WAITING AREA - MORNING</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="110bf73f-c190-411f-b362-e79869183ceb">
      <Text>Plastic chairs. A water cooler that gurgles like it's dying. A poster on the wall: "EVERY CHILD DESERVES A SAFE HOME" above a stock photo of a family that has never existed.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="162b62aa-04af-4552-8b9b-80bf3336a965">
      <Text>JAMIE McCORT sits. Barefoot. Hoodie. Hands in his lap. No one has asked him anything. A caseworker gave him a juice box forty minutes ago and hasn't come back.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="68dfe1d9-4490-4c7c-8c98-c9087fda9834">
      <Text>The juice box is untouched.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e1013dda-c180-48bc-8fe0-598366cd391d">
      <Text>He's not upset. He's confused. Specifically, he is confused about why he is here and not in handcuffs.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="cf0c54c3-89ae-4f45-9d07-4f54642b1a53">
      <Text>He keeps looking around for someone, anyone that understand how much evidence he just destroyed in his room when he saw them coming.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="663cb5da-e173-4c68-b1ef-6507954b88fe">
      <Text>He is, apparently, just a "minor in need of placement." Not a suspect. Not a person of interest. Just a child. A problem to be filed.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b973b9e4-eaf2-4d08-992c-9261db819d74">
      <Text>Through the glass partition to his left: two ACS ADMINISTRATORS at a desk, talking in the volume of people who have forgotten the walls are thin.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="e05d9843-8cf7-41ca-8390-1efef0c27132">
      <Text>ACS ADMIN #1</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b4dfb3b6-824a-466a-84ba-7c630f32e4ee">
      <Text>—the whole townhouse. Seized. Upper West Side, you should see this place. Four stories.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="d87a7d38-d6bb-4796-a0df-2adb36b12758">
      <Text>ACS ADMIN #2</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="652491ab-4b8a-4965-839e-cd79661ebb33">
      <Text>For what?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="e1dc6401-efeb-4f23-b26e-6a14119b32e8">
      <Text>ACS ADMIN #1</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="6f7497ae-9c15-4349-81bd-aed56e2d184d">
      <Text>Financial something. Securities fraud. It's the husband. Tech or medical something company guy. It's all over the news already.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="39a09e38-3593-42e9-934a-e6cfedf916ee">
      <Text>ACS ADMIN #2</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="ade727ad-a74b-4acb-a796-811b9b7108c8">
      <Text>And the mom?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c79a9b00-adf4-474a-b498-6237a8749b91">
      <Text>ACS ADMIN #1</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="18bbbbea-9dac-468d-b2b7-0de452dbaa12">
      <Text>Arrested too. She was the only one home when they came in.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="5b3227a5-14dd-4dfb-8ccf-98a4bdd1b1b0">
      <Text>ACS ADMIN #2</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="7d75f1e2-a22a-4cb7-9e17-84492259dd1d">
      <Text>Jesus. And we got the kid.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="8af5b565-2c72-4ef2-8159-98c2982608b8">
      <Text>ACS ADMIN #1</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="dcac4904-8e3e-411e-a962-53042e2fde44">
      <Text>Fourteen. No shoes. Just standing on the sidewalk when the caseworker got there. None of the neighbors said they knew him well enough to get involved.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="da7851bd-5fa2-4a5d-9497-ff056ca41ca1">
      <Text>ACS ADMIN #2</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="9dcf2770-5ccb-46ec-913c-8bc5c04771ba">
      <Text>Siblings?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="703b4d6c-0923-430e-bd51-325ad341a05a">
      <Text>He picks up the juice box. Takes a sip. Sets it down.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d66ab4bf-5eff-48d9-9d98-e344b9987fdb">
      <Text>Keeps waiting.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="d4f889d6-0930-49aa-ab8f-ee79aac34649">
      <SceneProperties Length="3 4/8" Page="14" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHET">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DUI GUY">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEVIN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MARCUS">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="PHIL">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="STEVE">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. CENTRAL BOOKING - PHONE BANK - MORNING</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="cca13239-4c68-4a78-8a5b-5d7142464297">
      <Text>A row of wall-mounted phones with short metal cords. The receivers are greasy with the residue of ten thousand desperate calls.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5a211ffe-1035-421f-ab76-9c72fe5a61de">
      <Text>KEVIN stands at the phone. Still in the suit. Ink still wet on his fingers. He dials from memory. He knows this number the way he knows his own birthday.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="309ff39f-41ff-4bb1-b6ed-ee5b81bdc436">
      <Text>It rings. Picks up.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="12564ef0-1fab-45a2-98ed-e4bfdfd293b8">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="75bc7a53-5d2a-4347-a0c5-a75a00bcf591">
      <Text>Marcus, it's Kevin. I need you to—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="cb71e08f-ed54-4dc6-a149-2e43e6342ed5">
      <Text>MARCUS (O.S.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="30e15d62-951e-4a85-a637-75c49f152689">
      <Text>Kevin. Stop.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="5e065f78-6b36-4089-b9a5-7ebaf3d0e1ca">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="bcfce33d-a170-4d49-9826-ad906a013750">
      <Text>I'm at Central Booking. I need representation immediately. I—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="1c59797f-711e-4fe1-9be4-98e73a0a9544">
      <Text>MARCUS (O.S.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="8a4f8059-a19c-431f-8d6f-85fe12d6b1d9">
      <Text>Kevin. I can't. We represent the company.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="1d0d75a5-aa58-495b-a57a-87b1111005f3">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="374f33f7-8eb7-4563-9b83-4f0308eee5d8">
      <Text>I know you represent the company. I'm the COO of the company.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="330b8d8e-559e-488a-9bb7-379df826d4bd">
      <Text>MARCUS (O.S.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="16ceb1d6-781e-4dfd-949f-c1bc531691e2">
      <Text>That's the problem. The firm represents MedAnalytic. You're being charged in connection with actions taken at MedAnalytic. You're adverse to our client.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="fa1fddd4-99e1-490e-9c5e-7fb7f6f893bf">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="fc3836ba-12c3-4aba-bab0-621c294eb4b8">
      <Text>I AM your client.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c8e8178e-5a53-42e9-95f8-af8229d096fc">
      <Text>MARCUS (O.S.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="bbdce7fa-bd35-4e0d-8450-88a49810103c">
      <Text>The company is our client. Not you personally. Kevin, I'm sorry. I can't even be on this call.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="833f350f-78a1-4648-b434-5a7f06617b05">
      <Text>Click.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="aa4db195-ce70-4f9c-8a7e-da88f2364883">
      <Text>Kevin stares at the phone. Dials again.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="0107df0c-0e6a-4eda-bb73-0a086edda706">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="903cccea-1ee5-48f5-be1c-1ec257943b15">
      <Text>Phil. It's Kevin McCort. I need—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c67c613c-97e1-4c6f-a5cb-a05204fea69b">
      <Text>PHIL (O.S.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="3944c9de-968f-4973-a03e-dc6950d282c4">
      <Text>Kev. Jesus. I saw the news. Listen, I wish I could help but we do outside counsel for MedAnalytic's regulatory compliance division. Conflict.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="fca76f06-0eeb-4215-991a-c58213558081">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="6a218840-8283-47e4-9790-9d3b9f6705e4">
      <Text>You're not even on the same—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="57b6e5aa-5201-493b-a583-54a39bb501ff">
      <Text>PHIL (O.S.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="de549a7d-6d5d-4a94-83c0-362d177ffc96">
      <Text>Doesn't matter. Same entity. I can't touch it. Call Brendan at—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="7c589dad-4e61-4158-9934-f9a2a10a094a">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e57127a9-5a52-43b0-a30c-785d3b7e0764">
      <Text>Brendan handles our European filings.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="cd937fe1-de71-47dd-8be3-e07b948f5104">
      <Text>PHIL (O.S.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="031c05d5-9b92-4fa2-a7b2-338ad847e3b9">
      <Text>Then he's out too. Kev, I gotta go. Good luck.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5765d2fa-b5e0-46c2-85db-f880669f58ab">
      <Text>Click.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f0138f22-bde4-456f-83ec-0d69274b2488">
      <Text>Kevin dials again. Faster now.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="3f154094-66d2-47e4-8e77-4102737d10c8">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f3e6d145-8af7-4a0a-95d8-ca1abd022923">
      <Text>Steve. Kevin McCort. I need criminal defense counsel immediately.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="1bc1544f-0e41-4987-9c44-7415db2bf4d5">
      <Text>STEVE (O.S.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e44fc496-b9ac-44f1-9c49-e05f58885c6a">
      <Text>Kevin, my firm just got retained by MedAnalytic's board twenty minutes ago. For the internal investigation. I can't—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c1c866ad-08de-4d3e-9095-e1e7ae7e5729">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="ed6a375a-7556-4e08-b1ba-c84e6598c94a">
      <Text>The board retained you? Already?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="5656fd32-19b3-41f9-a60c-c5a31f1fd30a">
      <Text>STEVE (O.S.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="5b6e957d-84c6-46c0-b7ea-1a471c5a088f">
      <Text>Chet called first thing this morning.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3c617e18-1c7f-4856-8497-dfb207a44baf">
      <Text>Kevin's hand tightens on the receiver.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="9c531cbd-0578-49dc-83aa-d68fe027fcb4">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="fc5808de-b6be-46b1-a787-65a521358352">
      <Text>Chet called. This morning.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f11e4163-f919-400e-b707-fa806239b117">
      <Text>STEVE (O.S.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="1974ff4c-be98-4c1e-97c4-9b9b580e9fb2">
      <Text>Kev. I'm sorry.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="220b2462-096e-49a0-b3ca-4ca4f6e2a24e">
      <Text>Click.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1f310b11-3bb3-4817-8d0b-a1cb5c557efd">
      <Text>He stands there. Chet called. First thing. Before Kevin's mugshot was dry. The board already lawyering up. Not for Kevin. Against Kevin.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e8bd502d-e136-4edb-9ac9-988fa00f3fd8">
      <Text>He dials one more number. This one slower. Reaching further back.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="0266b8e1-4e05-49f3-8fbc-9b7f8a06c7f9">
      <Text>It rings. Rings. Picks up.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="abe9d103-ff88-4de3-89ce-fd06c8e0b30f">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="62fb6af7-6d39-4715-a7b9-f9ed39122eb1">
      <Text>Chet.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c1aa63ba-af4c-4488-96b5-654c7c9a944f">
      <Text>CHET (O.S.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="3ca7cd57-1540-4bc3-983a-f1115083adea">
      <Text>(a pause that's one beat too long)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="be91d203-4d0f-4a03-9f4f-3b1600b5cce8">
      <Text>Kevin. Christ. Are you okay?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="18fca8cf-580b-4c00-b3e4-94321cac0447">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="1a653de1-4bab-4c01-8177-7cecf4338719">
      <Text>I'm at Central Booking. I need you to call Davidson and Howell and get them down here. I need—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="5115da78-31d5-4fa4-bbe2-46a8bee4a422">
      <Text>CHET (O.S.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="c1024d16-6b11-40e6-9f9f-89e5992e507d">
      <Text>Kev. Davidson is representing the company now. The board voted an hour ago. Emergency session. I can't—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="24c03fcc-0173-4535-a8bb-a357c4d3010d">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="bd169500-7d7e-4460-882e-e3cb8c3fb721">
      <Text>YOU called them. Steve just told me. You retained them this morning.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="5870fe53-9efd-4a46-b470-0a464c86662b">
      <Text>CHET (O.S.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="8db6bff2-89b2-47c0-bd05-9ea635c1f558">
      <Text>As board chair, Kevin. I had a fiduciary obligation to—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="11abe0c0-1698-48e3-9be1-07f7e647eb5f">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b1ded3eb-44b9-414c-8553-0e3e3c3cc21e">
      <Text>You're my fraternity brother.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="065f8772-523b-484a-ab90-bd8514f11fc7">
      <Text>A beat. The silence on the line has a texture. It sounds like money protecting itself.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c2ac9fac-56be-4289-b179-6fedd618d3dd">
      <Text>CHET (O.S.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="92598e83-41bb-42e1-a4ad-41aa2c4ab217">
      <Text>And as your fraternity brother, I'm telling you: get a lawyer. A personal one. Someone who isn't connected to any of this.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="7a817643-10d7-4e60-9da3-f37cd94f0ac8">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="7441727e-0712-46c0-abc6-b3e34fb5408c">
      <Text>(quiet, the rage just starting to curdle into something else)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f26921b3-c426-48bd-9ac8-579fb650410f">
      <Text>Connected to any of what, Chet.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a24d927a-6a43-4c48-af62-b89ed5808904">
      <Text>CHET (O.S.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a049f746-cd5e-46f9-ae76-9231e4391809">
      <Text>Kevin. I have to go. The board is reconvening in ten minutes.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="d0ff5e36-33d8-4627-9bf8-08ae53d6c6f6">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="67d20932-339a-438e-b50f-7c0747efe3a1">
      <Text>Chet—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ae680a90-5e40-4171-b14c-a18925741016">
      <Text>CHET (O.S.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="d173579b-d2a5-4a82-91c6-4be9c3b84607">
      <Text>Get a lawyer, Kev.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ba5dcd9e-fea6-487d-9554-970b0af1b2ee">
      <Text>Click.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6014ee18-6874-466a-9041-3f73a87355ff">
      <Text>Kevin holds the receiver. The dial tone drones. A man behind him clears his throat—waiting for the phone.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6f631c53-b2df-4bce-879b-09a8bccb2997">
      <Text>Kevin hangs up. Walks back to the metal bench. Sits.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f8b68430-ec31-4031-b7ec-6ff4761eab6b">
      <Text>The </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">DUI</Text>
      <Text> guy is still there. Chewing gum.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="6f17a0a0-28a6-4d1b-9b32-f9da88363301">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">DUI</Text>
      <Text> GUY</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="d013cdf5-fe37-44b6-ac47-ec66f3ce124e">
      <Text>Gum?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="b3f5a5f3-1322-4dc9-a02d-02848f200242">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="28f50746-5c70-4b9d-afc0-35bafe583b94">
      <Text>(barely audible)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e6a45b47-59de-40b2-bf38-0f166ebab7ff">
      <Text>Yeah.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="82e37f57-1a20-40a2-a5c1-0daadc2fe58f">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 7/8" Page="18" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHUCKLES">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAZ">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. CHUCKLES' APARTMENT - 5TH FLOOR - MORNING</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b63ff829-97db-41df-88d0-321ce3fb4236">
      <Text>Five flights. No elevator. The stairwell smells like curry and meth lab chemicals on the fourth floor that Jaz doesn't investigate.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="06438250-3a0e-4ceb-9a04-b55dfce4b9f5">
      <Text>She knocks. The door opens on a chain. One bloodshot eye. Moving too fast.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a338c555-6568-4b9c-b256-e01dabe83eef">
      <Text>CHUCKLES</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="78bf4c22-6f15-4921-85c5-69069666101d">
      <Text>(rapid, paranoid)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="bb1ed234-ec5b-4e87-a81a-57f2520632e2">
      <Text>Why are you here. Did Declan send you. Is this about Detroit.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="0f6432e6-cfa0-42d9-8446-68a21bf2d24e">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="958c2cd6-e328-4dcc-90a7-2e457ea83e86">
      <Text>Open the door, Chuckles.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c4a129de-4245-4c93-8eb4-d4de511fd7df">
      <Text>The chain slides.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a7abfe6e-90a1-4785-884a-18f150e90ba3">
      <Text>THE APARTMENT: a railroad one-bedroom that was charming in 2004. Concert posters thumbtacked to the walls— some genuine vintage, Black Flag, Dead Kennedys, Minor Threat— the remnants of a pedigree that expired sometime during the Obama administration.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9fd23f73-1b1e-4137-bacf-8be20b312447">
      <Text>On the couch— once nice, tufted, mid-century, now swaybacked and cigarette- burned— STACY one of the COKE LADIES OF THE NIGHT from the green room. She's in a deep heroin nod, chin on her chest, mouth slack. Next to her on the cushion, a rig. The needle still wet. A thin line of blood seeping from the crook of her arm onto the upholstery, blooming slow into the fabric like a flower nobody planted.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c9f0378c-41f2-437e-94ba-5eb910be2ff9">
      <Text>In the corner by the window, on a stand: a 1972 Les Paul Custom. Black. The gold hardware gone green at the edges. The frets worn silver in the first five positions from years of the same hand in the same places. It is the single cleanest thing in the apartment.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6ccbd39b-28d2-4a81-9266-dfb48f09d727">
      <Text>CHUCKLES stands in the middle of the room. Faded Misfits shirt— original, not reprint, the one credential he has left. Jaw grinding. Pupils like dinner plates. He has not slept.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="60516124-228d-4d56-b3b8-706c8fb931a5">
      <Text>CHUCKLES</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="2f456be9-1efe-459e-a2cd-d2388f0dd4c4">
      <Text>Phoenix. In my apartment. Holy shit. Can I get you something? Water? I think I have water.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="02ee7305-d793-407b-ba37-0af353ccd668">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f156892e-b243-4059-85aa-212955c54811">
      <Text>I need a shower. And something to wear that isn't this.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f1542d25-efa8-4010-9f0b-afe591d0daa2">
      <Text>She gestures at herself. The suit jacket. The harness. The booty shorts. Too many hours since she slept or changed.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b8d5a3d7-7c4b-4574-b796-b0a4813763b6">
      <Text>Chuckles' eyes light up. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="11902405-1558-4619-b38f-25c29cc033ed">
      <Text>CHUCKLES</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="165e6a24-ebfd-4374-8c86-7e5fd6be6eaf">
      <Text>Oh! Oh great! Yeah!</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b78298e7-f4ca-441d-b84a-71f7b2a270a9">
      <Text>Saucer plate eyes rapid shifting between her and Stacy.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="10d0e171-7330-4647-80e5-60446afda189">
      <Text>CHUCKLES</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="0fcaa77f-f87a-4402-b5f5-b6c6c1f66c20">
      <Text>Shower, right! Great!</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="09966c8c-dbdc-4c10-9dd4-095865abd4de">
      <Text>(Coke brain grinding)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="06c4c149-cf57-4514-8bfe-8c407c01cce9">
      <Text>What if I take some photos? Of you. Like in the shower. For my feed. Nothing weird- Like punk </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">vérité</Text>
      <Text>. Phoenix in repose. Or— you and Stacy—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="207a3dda-3f6b-479d-b558-3f4d11011afc">
      <Text>He gestures at the couch. Stacy's chin dips further. The blood on the cushion spreads another quarter inch.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="0760d8da-6078-48f8-bf86-2cd5cb776f23">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a84f72b0-c78f-41c7-b29d-a16ced522bb9">
      <Text>Shirt, Chuckles.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="57fff71a-d42c-4415-b733-1382d801ce10">
      <Text>CHUCKLES</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="ec338a93-7a11-42a8-a6b6-aad9a6ecd034">
      <Text>(instantly deflating)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="98c56e86-f25e-46ac-b22a-3d2be404de1b">
      <Text>Right. Yeah. Respect. Boundaries.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e505a501-3c4a-4b8a-8a50-33e7261b90d4">
      <Text>He disappears into the bedroom. Returns with a faded black Ramones tee. Presidential seal logo. Soft from a hundred washes.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="1ad7d357-b335-4795-bb59-fb305505b79c">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="8248d0f5-1e66-4210-977e-568f5b7bda36">
      <Text>This works. Shower?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="96efd178-0fc8-4b00-a40b-374b1978b7a2">
      <Text>CHUCKLES</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="550c43b0-5e78-49f2-a3a8-a7b0d71a06a7">
      <Text>Down the hall. Jiggle the left handle. Don't use the towel that's in there. I'll find you one.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="611e8ae8-585a-473c-850b-7e5ac0b82088">
      <Text>She takes the shirt and walks down the narrow hall.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="eb0d6e5c-332b-4b0e-9b2d-e5a1ffa06536">
      <SceneProperties Length="7/8" Page="20" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. CHUCKLES' BATHROOM - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="507a6b63-3270-4f3a-a2cb-fe890d1bd804">
      <Text>Small. Tile that was white once. A mirror she doesn't look in. She strips. The suit jacket. The harness. The booty shorts. The fishnets. Peels it all off and drops it on the floor like a skin she's shedding.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3c188705-2a07-48d1-884d-bbb371cda276">
      <Text>She turns the handle. Jiggles left. The pipes bang once, twice, and then—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3007d8c5-980d-4229-bb31-3648e01ff169">
      <Text>Hot water.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8c6b0158-2b7b-4855-82a2-0179888b8ef9">
      <Text>It hits her and she stops. Just stands there. Eyes closed. Hands at her sides. Not washing. Not moving. Just letting it land.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2e66650b-6390-4bb8-b0a1-bc4d498e1ea8">
      <Text>For thirty seconds, the world melts away.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="bb08af6e-2735-4672-b847-13e7d2ef20c1">
      <Text>She's just a body in hot water. And it's enough.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5e9b9765-6eb3-4822-ad09-707842528d89">
      <Text>Her shoulders drop. Her jaw unclenches. The muscles across her back release something they've been holding since she saw the flashing lights on West 84th.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b7f7766f-4267-4433-b025-38c980fad4bb">
      <Text>Thirty seconds. That's all she takes.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9c68aea2-1064-4916-bdd8-d40601333c02">
      <Text>Then her eyes open. She washes. Fast. Efficient. Whatever soap is in here. Whatever shampoo. It doesn't matter.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7ac9a0e7-e4eb-4c7d-be37-eafc63b4b6d8">
      <Text>She's done in four minutes. Out. Dripping on the tile.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="223dda52-dfd7-42ac-b4d9-79a328ad4fc1">
      <Text>She pulls on the Ramones shirt. It's too big. Hits her mid- thigh. She looks like a girl who borrowed her boyfriend's shirt after staying the night.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5b9b187b-6320-4e32-b0b4-fe00e7a46ad8">
      <Text>For 2 seconds she looks like a teenager.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8a4224e3-050b-44e8-81d6-51a1fc500cdc">
      <Text>For 2 seconds Phoenix is gone.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="cbc8df8c-da40-4667-b999-367ace822170">
      <Text>She catches herself in the mirror. She could pass for someone a caseworker might trust.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f20f6e31-ab10-4d4e-99bb-02e05d8885e3">
      <Text>She picks up the messenger bag—it came into the bathroom with her, it goes everywhere with her— and walks back down the hall.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="149583ac-ea1f-4387-a70c-a3c712d0d905">
      <SceneProperties Length="1" Page="20" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CORRECTIONS OFFICER">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. CENTRAL BOOKING - WOMEN'S PROCESSING - MORNING</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8abb7ca2-6b62-4cac-a586-4d6d862719b3">
      <Text>A room the size of a closet. Cold. A female CORRECTIONS OFFICER with a clipboard and the expression of someone who does this forty times a day.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9940c847-bb9d-4ba0-a3e0-acd645e2614e">
      <Text>JANET stands on the marked line in the floor. They've taken the Lululemon. It's in a bag with her name on it. She's in a paper gown that should tie in the back and but doesn't.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="6366c66c-38b1-4533-a43e-293cdcbd1feb">
      <Text>CORRECTIONS OFFICER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="8be9fe8d-81d6-4354-999d-a088904f1899">
      <Text>Gown off.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="655a09b5-92ef-47a9-8f08-7440a4c4d49c">
      <Text>Janet unties it. Lets it fall. Stands there. Naked under fluorescent light that flatters nothing. All of it on display for a woman with a clipboard who couldn't care less.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="7c5c2c33-f1ce-4fa9-be01-c256b9162e0e">
      <Text>CORRECTIONS OFFICER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="7782a40e-f7a0-432b-893c-2a3c3373f551">
      <Text>Arms up. Turn around.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="23a91bb7-ccd2-462b-86b2-94d0608fcdf8">
      <Text>Janet complies. Slow. Precise. The way she does everything.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ee76d4e9-42ef-41d7-99fa-033f0ff31495">
      <Text>CORRECTIONS OFFICER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b3e09834-cdda-4910-bfb5-63a0da1074fb">
      <Text>Bend forward. Spread. Cough.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9a5a6cf3-3198-4c41-b26a-b47cf89d573f">
      <Text>Janet bends. Spreads. Coughs.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="fa3d9d27-4a51-4cd2-8559-0ea8367e97e7">
      <Text>Her face is turned toward the wall. Cinder block. Someone scratched FUCK YOU into it with a fingernail.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="639da04a-13c0-4cfb-8015-d852b9f70232">
      <Text>She coughs again. Her eyes are dry.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="2aae902d-a5ba-460f-8821-b10c9fc02ad1">
      <Text>CORRECTIONS OFFICER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e79a089e-379d-4d48-8423-b25a8c416f9f">
      <Text>Again.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="aa7702fc-a8de-4a73-9409-378ed7f01f16">
      <Text>She coughs again.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ea49f23c-5dd2-4336-aed5-ec4a59bca3a3">
      <Text>CORRECTIONS OFFICER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="c0d7196e-ee62-4dbf-9012-805c52600b3b">
      <Text>Stand up. Arms out.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b4b0bb11-fbb0-4f06-b54d-3704193f47a5">
      <Text>The officer runs a gloved hand through Janet's hair. Checks behind her ears. Under her arms. Between her toes. Clinical. Thorough.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="35a7f1da-8993-4e91-abc1-997a32651c3f">
      <Text>CORRECTIONS OFFICER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="c1be9422-125a-49a0-84f7-46e0c4fad1f4">
      <Text>Get dressed. Holding is through that door.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2235e01c-e453-48fa-a29c-b2176e2dda8a">
      <Text>Janet picks up the gown. Puts it back on. Ties it. The knot is perfect.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="04e42678-26df-4b5f-bee1-fed1343566c8">
      <Text>She has not said a word. Her expression has not betrayed a single feeling.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="0351c5eb-1a5e-45bf-9072-609a6ba0f3c1">
      <SceneProperties Length="3" Page="21" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHUCKLES">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAZ">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. CHUCKLES' APARTMENT - LIVING ROOM - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="dd35064f-0b59-4ba6-972b-e63f55aff1e0">
      <Text>Stacy hasn't moved. The blood has stopped spreading. Reached its frontier. Chuckles has put a dish towel on the cushion next to the rig. His version of first aid.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="32d10e55-7e4c-4ca4-aa28-26523caeec16">
      <Text>He's at the kitchen counter rolling a cigarette when Jaz comes back. He looks at her. Does a double take. Without the harness and the leather and the war paint, she's a different person. She's a kid.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="2b3a1f14-2cac-43ea-bca7-e1e3dec4bb13">
      <Text>CHUCKLES</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="d0a27417-e92d-4a27-b159-bbb465a04d54">
      <Text>Whoa. You look... different.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a079fda6-bca3-46b0-984f-a32938d1d271">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="46188e62-efc5-456f-b50d-ead9883f59b9">
      <Text>I need something else.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ee1d82a2-03bf-4109-b46c-5df7254e7d9e">
      <Text>She reaches into the messenger bag. Pulls out a folded piece of paper. Printed. Stained—the printer it came from lives on a card table in a basement on St. Marks. It's a residential lease agreement. Standard New York boilerplate. Both their names. This address.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8b7292f5-f613-453d-91cd-0a6035783f4f">
      <Text>She unfolds it on the counter.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="34f8f4fc-7104-456c-ad81-86a2c6825bc3">
      <Text>CHUCKLES</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="3ba9c64d-6771-4822-bdd6-bec70d53283f">
      <Text>What is this.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="84f962dd-ccca-4190-8f34-324bf2a4a120">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b3a22679-00a0-46d5-b6f5-7778b98cf148">
      <Text>A lease. For this apartment. Both our names. Dated four months ago.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="371ee4f5-3fa0-4629-abec-122efc530fd7">
      <Text>CHUCKLES</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="24bf3be0-08f1-44f0-a0d3-0407fe606b85">
      <Text>We don't have a—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a6c15045-4410-4dd1-b34c-805877372f27">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="762739e6-0c9e-4639-ade0-aca3f32d9745">
      <Text>We do now. If anyone calls, we've been together four months. Very very much in love. Very happy.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="2aab2d81-19f9-421a-82b2-1cf04754142f">
      <Text>CHUCKLES</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a31c971e-e6de-4aaa-9e0b-f7b8a7708df5">
      <Text>In love. You and me.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="b9996282-00cd-48b7-8ed5-25bb93e28a3f">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="cc1bd076-072c-43cc-9cd7-895a138af25f">
      <Text>And we would love to take in my little brother. Drive him to school every morning. Feed him three balanced meals every day.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="71978e93-ea54-498e-b4a7-7637e5462402">
      <Text>CHUCKLES</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f7b49e32-0579-4b6f-9e77-f6b69b1f231b">
      <Text>Your brother?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="756fea56-96b9-48df-9124-d45db8c2ea30">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="98bfc888-f184-4b78-b606-a958172462a1">
      <Text>He's fourteen. He's in ACS right now because my parents got arrested and I need an address. A real address with a lease.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="198e2624-75d1-4a08-8c57-ab2b3b7e98ec">
      <Text>Chuckles looks at the lease. His jaw is grinding but something behind it is thinking.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="049582f5-e105-406a-bb07-0126fd2dd5d0">
      <Text>CHUCKLES</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="6a57b3f0-2156-45bb-8274-b85dd5d55c61">
      <Text>I don't know, Phoenix. This is— this is like, government shit. Lying to the government. That's—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="8378ef19-9b47-4122-a854-952dd8267d2e">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="657a54b5-a113-40a5-8c27-f393aaa47cd4">
      <Text>I'll cover rent while I'm here.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="456e8aae-c686-44a3-8723-a5abea1199b5">
      <Text>CHUCKLES</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="340cec7f-fc6b-4083-ab91-3b46b806aa36">
      <Text>It's not about the money.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d400fa8d-5b9e-42bd-b57b-0c5b6cd6ecb7">
      <Text>And here is the thing about Jaz.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="dd7c83c7-226a-4c80-b2f2-419596d287e2">
      <Text>She can look at a poker table and read every hand from the sweat patterns. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2d213281-ccc9-4936-aeb9-e8b8c3e31a6e">
      <Text>She can look into someone's eyes and see the thing they value most— not the thing they say, not the thing they perform, but the actual thing they want and want to be. The one they'd trade everything else for.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="76a75a19-e4a8-4770-bbae-a59e9d59f8fd">
      <Text>She looks at Chuckles.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d96bc134-984c-45dd-828e-52b7f9f1c3b6">
      <Text>She sees the original faded Misfits shirt. The posters on the wall. Not decoration—documentation. Proof of attendance. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7f45c48f-3d8c-4773-993e-406dbee654a6">
      <Text>She sees a man who peaked in a scene that moved on without him. Who wakes up every day in a faded shirt from a show he was at and tries to matter to people who don't need him.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="48337d96-388e-4b44-b411-18fa1ade5022">
      <Text>She sees what he actually wants. And it isn't money. And it isn't photos for his feed.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="476999af-2659-49b2-9b86-0e083fc9014b">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="6393292e-aef7-460e-b008-6b8930a8ddb9">
      <Text>(quiet, direct, no angle)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="9ce5678e-a75f-4dd2-9600-e46d07b14ca4">
      <Text>Chuckles. Look at me.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6becfdeb-7ed0-4c55-a96b-490ce857cbc8">
      <Text>He looks at her.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ec39ba26-cbee-4fec-afef-f13a36772dfb">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="9947d5ea-ca6d-4f53-aed9-4be94e819cf4">
      <Text>You know you're a good guy, right?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="98f0e717-781f-4960-8820-b2f0ed6b0a48">
      <Text>He blinks. His jaw stops grinding for the first time since she walked in.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="6c854e9c-a64d-425b-9ed5-c4b8ac35d9a2">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="926bb15d-baf9-44d6-923a-7597f0280794">
      <Text>I know you think nobody sees it. But I do.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="d006706c-eff4-423d-ad6c-b50e6bde4503">
      <Text>CHUCKLES</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="c10785c9-4c1d-45b1-b7e6-d352f4e284b3">
      <Text>(quiet)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="7f245596-e1a3-4735-af55-d3225625332d">
      <Text>Yea—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="0f75ea58-d003-405f-9d02-49bfd4505b8d">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="182dca27-da9d-4f91-a6ca-ed38e2015b69">
      <Text>You're a good guy. And right now my little brother is sitting in a government office on the edge of getting lost in a system. He needs a hero. You could be our hero.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5f37e613-6cbd-4f50-80f1-a3d059858022">
      <Text>She holds his gaze. No seduction. No threat. No play. Just the truth, delivered to someone who almost never hears it.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="2be0d303-7a8e-4e48-b4c3-c0ebcf3520c2">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="2579f6f3-2a3c-4139-8dce-77ceb2bca46c">
      <Text>And when this is done, and it's three in the morning, and you're alone. When the coke's worn off, and you're lying on that couch staring at the ceiling. And that wondering of if YOU are still someone worth being— you'll know. You still have that hero in you, that in all of this shit- you can still actually care about doing the right and kind thing.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="250ac393-a1c6-427c-a33c-936dfedc9254">
      <Text>Chuckles doesn't move. The apartment is quiet except for Stacy's shallow breathing and the traffic on Avenue D.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b0571570-c52e-4ec0-9d3c-942106845285">
      <Text>His eyes are wet. Just barely. He'll deny it later.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f794d01b-4cab-4e66-ae4c-de3a04a281d9">
      <Text>He picks up a pen. A Sharpie, from a jar on the counter. He signs the lease. Dates it March 12th. Slides it back.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4ccc86ea-2e61-4675-bde8-5fb9c329c0f9">
      <Text>CHUCKLES</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="82b28a23-bda4-4143-896f-6486589fff00">
      <Text>(rough, clearing his throat)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b1069ac1-a1f2-4d12-9b8b-305a794ea752">
      <Text>If they call, we're in love. Four months. Happiest I've ever been.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="7c918506-8a61-4f0b-84d4-ec506f185d75">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="c0323e11-f0e4-48e4-8425-156da7712696">
      <Text>You sell it like that and I might actually believe you.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="dc13ff56-a93b-4945-bbda-4be0987bad34">
      <Text>She folds the lease. Puts it in the bag. Tosses him Tanner's suit jacket and shirt.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a1556acf-be97-4170-a600-6f6e08ea6f4e">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="181b2bca-a5ec-4ad4-8662-65f4aa53c88a">
      <Text>Now, I need pants.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="73ccd3f8-e99d-4a07-9887-eafacbf88e72">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="24" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. CHINATOWN - MORNING</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6899c829-f963-4d37-96a1-681479420873">
      <Text>JAZ moves fast. Ramones tee. Wet hair. Black skinny jeans. Combat boots. Messenger bag. She's been awake for twenty-eight hours and she's moving like she just started.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="a168eeb2-3e6b-4d7a-a92e-c37a8b786ce4">
      <SceneProperties Length="2 1/8" Page="25" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAZ">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MR. CHEN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. WANG'S AUTHENTIC NOODLE - MORNING</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c627a377-cbd3-4d87-a4f5-055a01f63327">
      <Text>Three knocks. Pause. Two more.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3087ead5-941d-4e2f-beb6-b5c04ea62512">
      <Text>The locks click. The door opens. MR. CHEN peers out. Cigarette still fused to his lip. He looks at her. Looks at the Ramones shirt. Looks at her face.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="fd81b072-bd09-4f89-b427-5d0c97423fa6">
      <Text>MR. CHEN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="0b7d5c08-ea91-49f6-84e9-6bea38cde39b">
      <Text>You look different.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="0ff9afaa-888f-40dc-939b-4543a5e9036e">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="87194a20-619a-462c-93d7-151c7fcc02b1">
      <Text>I need to cash out. The last of the chips from last night. Now.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="1bca35eb-671d-49de-885d-d53e273ac0b9">
      <Text>MR. CHEN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="cfc7623b-cc2c-42bc-93df-fc6e78164e37">
      <Text>Come.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="bb8e1b1f-e984-4f81-b511-e1d49f6eea18">
      <Text>She follows him through the dark restaurant. Past the counter. Through the kitchen. The hanging carcasses brush her shoulders as she passes— ducks, pigs... yes, just pigs. And deeper in, past the reach of the health inspector's flashlight, shapes she doesn't recognize. Organs in buckets. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e5184c3d-6076-48a8-94a0-16ea6da0a2ce">
      <Text>Mr. Chen leads her to a small desk in the back. He sits. She sets the bag down. Pulls out the remaining chips.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4ce676fa-1348-4976-aae7-07b2f1869d88">
      <Text>He counts them. Fast. His fingers moving with the speed of a man who has been counting things since the dawn of time.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="6529c720-f516-42df-b141-0fef3136746e">
      <Text>MR. CHEN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="348bf8b6-0859-4e0d-822f-9274e8647fd8">
      <Text>Forty-seven thousand. After the house cut.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f4c6eeaf-3395-458a-8d00-678ff5ddaaff">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="14c028db-b4e5-4be2-abde-b4183f83b2f8">
      <Text>Fine.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="fea029e1-5fb3-4b4d-b0f3-45b714b5fc9a">
      <Text>He opens a drawer. Pulls out banded cash. Counts it out on the desk between the carcasses and the grease.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="043b4546-cc1e-4af4-98b9-69a350badf27">
      <Text>MR. CHEN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="57f0444c-48b6-4b06-829c-e0986030a28b">
      <Text>Jimmy Fong has a message.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="922024f9-d19a-4414-80be-52482ba27226">
      <Text>His hand stays on the money.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="57ee56c4-ff67-4985-9562-446a3935daa8">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="074cf2c2-e9b0-45c3-8860-5e846d6a3ccb">
      <Text>I'm sure he does.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="cac25cb2-396a-47ff-ad4c-7dca124887fd">
      <Text>MR. CHEN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="848c3026-94b9-433d-892c-e3ff43faf58a">
      <Text>He is not happy. He is asking for his property returned.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="0b019546-8b25-49ab-879c-58d43cea96ba">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="941a70fb-bde4-4bfe-b2d5-e662d5614689">
      <Text>His property. He put it on the table. I won it clean.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="66a5dc55-9e70-47da-8edf-d0849140e6a3">
      <Text>MR. CHEN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="d524e4b3-3a3d-41fa-907a-61ed071ec58e">
      <Text>I know this. You know this.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="fad25201-1f71-409b-8c84-ae6c349d965a">
      <Text>He looks at her. And something shifts. The grumbling old man from the noodle shop is gone. What's underneath is older. Quieter. The voice doesn't change, but the weight of it does—like a whisper backed by a cathedral.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="3bb65d97-e2b0-46e8-b89d-19581c9ac172">
      <Text>MR. CHEN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="429f5c81-ffa2-48a6-ab0f-b7191f31b769">
      <Text>The transaction was deemed sound after review. The bet was ruled good.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="2bfb9a0a-77aa-4d48-a23d-7c748d8394db">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="5c85755b-43ed-4a7c-a7ad-62f1662bf9cb">
      <Text>Ruled. By who.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4bd48188-60bc-459c-b3b5-c1c83cb9cc4c">
      <Text>Mr. Chen doesn't answer. He removes his hand from the money. Pushes it toward her.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4607eb29-a6b8-4be6-abf9-0c002e5d6916">
      <Text>Around them, the carcasses hang. The kitchen is silent in a way that kitchens in Chinatown are never silent. As if the room itself is holding its breath because someone in it just spoke on behalf of something that doesn't need to raise its voice.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="58d51d55-7904-4f05-a452-d7833ccdcd1f">
      <Text>MR. CHEN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="c7d95bd6-0f78-4513-bc4c-ab117b468b42">
      <Text>Jimmy will make noise. This is what Jimmy does. But he will not harm you. Not on this issue.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="eb4f8c6e-a77b-4b08-918a-4c95a6385d2c">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="2b43dcbc-9311-451f-966b-bd00ba7ac411">
      <Text>This matter is settled. I will advise you not to start a second.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="321815a5-aaab-4dcb-b1a4-57ad4908d1b3">
      <Text>Jaz takes the money. Puts it in the bag.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="faa9eee6-7ae5-4865-af27-353a64d25640">
      <Text>Mr. Chen reaches into the drawer again. Pulls out a manila envelope. Sets it on the desk. Slides it toward her.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3be27231-7b1e-40cc-952c-b5e4c4f0a082">
      <Text>Inside: a legal affidavit. Heavy bond paper. Embossed letterhead— WHITFIELD, PARK &amp; LIANG, with offices in Hong Kong, Singapore, San Francisco, and New York. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="12377323-f656-4ba0-8595-28c4e099d327">
      <Text>The document is a notarized transfer of ownership. The Playboy Resort and Entertainment Complex. Great Gorge, New Jersey. Into the name of Jasmine McCort. Witnessed, stamped, and filed.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="71864289-0829-4538-97d6-093bd0c33f04">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="5558c5eb-15c5-48a1-98d6-95ee378b2d21">
      <Text>How- Thank you, Mr. Chen.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="399a769b-1c8c-459b-b80e-8133b7262f33">
      <Text>MR. CHEN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="fc657ae3-2f1e-4c83-9b3b-1359d11d64d4">
      <Text>(already turning away, the old man persona returning)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="473695e5-5dbd-4785-b73a-cef616ba08a0">
      <Text>Don't come back for at least a month. You bad for business.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f25b4975-d33c-4d6e-88c3-dd496ed3caa8">
      <Text>She moves through the kitchen. Past the carcasses. Through the dark restaurant. Out the door.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="b9adf9fb-4450-454d-87f6-f166b2c012f3">
      <SceneProperties Length="6/8" Page="27" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TANNER">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. CHINATOWN - MR. CHEN'S BUILDING - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1f288f4a-2346-4d44-9cbf-15225a03706b">
      <Text>Daylight. The street waking up— fish markets hosing sidewalks, produce stands stacking </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">bok</Text>
      <Text> </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">choy</Text>
      <Text>, old women pulling carts over curbs.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4e762440-6278-4aa8-9a1b-b7ea9f75022b">
      <Text>Jaz steps onto the sidewalk. Messenger bag across her chest. $47,000 heavier. She turns north toward Canal—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="65fe4260-a635-41b2-abc0-75f5172555e6">
      <Text>TANNER (O.S.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="79a75cdb-44b2-4b66-8895-11d9cb736d1e">
      <Text>PHOENIX!</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a6d6a97a-d485-4bf3-bb39-a8b3f2bd34af">
      <Text>She doesn't turn. She walks faster.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="af13a755-7d60-4950-ab6e-f435150565b2">
      <Text>TANNER (O.S.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="30934d78-18c4-4eaa-983f-11eaea0f8257">
      <Text>GET HER!</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ac6ed32b-bd53-4a02-9f2b-e598708cc134">
      <Text>She looks back.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="cc0433b9-72a8-49e2-b910-c3961f3269bc">
      <Text>TANNER. Hospital gown. Tangerine thong. Paper slippers soaking through. Gauze on his left hand—brown-red, soaked, too flat where the pinky should be. He's been waiting outside since he got out of whatever hospital they dumped him at.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="193a1f0f-c65b-4ba0-9786-35a4e0be6927">
      <Text>And he's not alone.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="aa26ba0f-123a-46e3-af7e-8b9328bab6b8">
      <Text>THREE MEN. Jimmy Fong's guys. Not the A-team— the A-team</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="General" id="7d37b694-ab09-4e13-8c4d-71551fde30ef">
      <Text>took Tanner's finger. These are the C-team at best. Track pants and knock off Jordans.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="213d4266-8597-41e3-9e8f-dbcfb32b5cf8">
      <Text>They're already moving. Spreading out. One on the sidewalk. One cutting into the street. One coming straight at her.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5846c541-930c-47b6-86e5-3042ce151966">
      <Text>Jaz runs.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d7414451-8ea5-47e5-abc6-62a22dc6d2ea">
      <Text>A dead sprint north on Mott. The messenger bag slamming against her hip— the deed, the cash, everything.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="d41a029d-7e02-41a3-bb24-a8c360468b7b">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="28" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TANNER">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. MOTT STREET - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="fa77de59-d6f7-4d29-ac4e-6503901453c1">
      <Text>She's fast. Combat boots on wet pavement, arms pumping, weaving through the early morning foot traffic. An old man with a newspaper flattens against a wall as she blows past.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="bf7a7e03-90e6-43db-9beb-53538a545ebf">
      <Text>Behind her: Knockoffs on concrete. Three sets. Plus the wet slap of Tanner's paper slippers.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="fb6402e7-2a23-4f7f-87b1-7c398f9ede34">
      <Text>TANNER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="65b62657-1d35-4709-ae10-0397d8aae50f">
      <Text>(running, shouting)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="ff82b99c-63a1-4617-89c0-b9b93645b4fd">
      <Text>JUST GIVE IT BACK! JUST GIVE ME THE DEED!</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a3431658-66b7-4b8b-b2ec-87713f1dc4fe">
      <Text>She cuts left. Hard. Into the gap between a bakery and a dried goods shop. Shoulder clips the doorframe. Keeps moving.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="ec7d6791-b933-4929-88fd-39d2249c3692">
      <SceneProperties Length="6/8" Page="28" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="COOK">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TANNER">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT./INT. ALLEY / RESTAURANT KITCHEN - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="04434444-b538-4917-9058-418f7d34633f">
      <Text>The gap opens into a narrow alley. Dumpsters. Stacked crates. A kitchen door propped open with a milk crate, steam pouring out.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="af2c8f7c-84d7-41e9-bcf8-27d05a5d0bb2">
      <Text>She goes through it.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="80068767-acb7-4bb9-a7fd-742f30de4307">
      <Text>The kitchen of a dim sum restaurant at 7:45 AM. Full production. Six cooks. Bamboo steamers stacked four high. Woks on burners spitting oil. A prep table covered in dumpling skins.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e586d3a2-709c-4f6b-b9cf-daf1e5f7205c">
      <Text>Jaz barrels through. Ducks under a rack of hanging roast ducks. Knocks a tray of har </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">gow</Text>
      <Text> off a counter— the dumplings scatter across the tile like fat white marbles.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f5483430-0e54-494b-995d-f3ba64b72298">
      <Text>COOK</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="7d30e28b-3473-4a18-8ea7-7ea20c1c6121">
      <Text>(Cantonese, furious)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="ed9b368f-d831-4e3e-9c1f-65394fd35aa6">
      <Text>HEY! HEY!</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="747a2e3f-ac65-4a09-b745-837caeed62bc">
      <Text>She's through the kitchen in four seconds. Out the swinging door into the dining room. Chairs still on top of tables. She vaults over a booth— one hand on the divider, messenger bag swinging—and hits the front door.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="81ced0ae-00e0-4eb3-968e-316afa9a156c">
      <Text>Behind her: CRASH. One of Jimmy's guys comes through the kitchen. Hits the har </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">gow</Text>
      <Text>. His knock off Jordans find zero traction on dumpling skin and tile. He goes down. Takes a stack of steamers with him. Bamboo and shrimp everywhere.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="92e032c7-d67b-444d-81e4-45384ed18868">
      <Text>Two guys still coming. Plus Tanner.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="1f94f151-19fc-4ecb-9227-d6f702738ca5">
      <Text>TANNER (O.S.)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="846a339e-6280-47bc-a968-1a1d40fc0ea4">
      <Text>They took my FINGER, Phoenix. They took my fucking finger and that was just the FIRST ONE. Jimmy's going to—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="5ddd4a32-43e6-4c7d-8453-c407cac04d0f">
      <SceneProperties Length="4/8" Page="29" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JIMMY'S GUY #2">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. BAYARD STREET - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ab2b9743-f1d2-4d2e-926c-8d8a50e3634f">
      <Text>She's on Bayard now. The sidewalks thickening. Vendors setting up folding tables. A fish market rolling up its garage door— the smell hits the street like a wall.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2cd47cfc-b45a-413c-9c5a-d6ffa2a743cc">
      <Text>She runs through it. Uses the crowd. Drops her height. Rounds her shoulders. Tries to disappear.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5daedde4-8078-4d4d-8e5b-0aaa339d9c8a">
      <Text>Can't. The two remaining guys are fast. One is twenty feet back. The other has crossed the street and is running parallel, trying to cut her off at the next intersection.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="008f011e-c7eb-484f-bc22-2bb84e450174">
      <Text>JIMMY'S GUY #2</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="72c6bf90-dc9b-4903-a7ea-9c100df651da">
      <Text>(into phone, Cantonese, running)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="1559521b-2a94-4949-9bc4-984176f5ad6c">
      <Text>She's going east on Bayard—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="493bb261-8f59-4aec-8f7d-b3c79b191a74">
      <Text>Jaz sees the pincer. Sees the guy across the street angling toward the corner. She's going to get boxed.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="0c38902c-3a05-424b-8886-064b732a288c">
      <Text>She cuts right. Into a produce market. Through the front door past a woman weighing dragon fruit on a hanging scale.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="0ab64717-f771-43a9-8905-34ca16a807e6">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 4/8" Page="29" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAZ">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JIMMY'S GUY #2">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MADAM">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. PRODUCE MARKET / STAIRWELL - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c01de962-28a9-4bc1-be02-3347b7c8d9d0">
      <Text>The market is narrow and deep. Bins of ginger, lotus root, long beans in bundles. She runs the length of it. Customers pressing against the shelves as she passes.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="0f1d93c1-8d27-4b58-8d09-3f169aca05da">
      <Text>At the back: a door. A stairwell. She takes it.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5144ec67-5fe6-4ed1-b289-3b1d2cd28ae9">
      <Text>Up. Two steps at a time. The messenger bag bouncing. Her lungs burning. First floor. Second floor. The stairwell smells like five decades of cooking oil and cigarettes.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="54bb07bd-75bd-4986-afd8-e7ab616543ce">
      <Text>Below her: a door slamming open. Knock Offs on stairs.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="de35f6b3-be44-4833-bc95-53ce0019beae">
      <Text>JIMMY'S GUY #2</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="60352706-a24b-422f-9f62-9fcf79021ffd">
      <Text>(from below)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="ab4d8e99-0934-4390-984e-62a7920901f9">
      <Text>SHE WENT UP!</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="47009ca7-864b-4f37-b000-311f36efb16a">
      <Text>Third floor. A hallway. Linoleum. A fluorescent tube buzzing and flickering. The smell changes— jasmine oil and something chemical- sweet underneath it. A hand-painted sign on a door: "GOLDEN LOTUS WELLNESS SPA." Below it, in smaller letters: "BY APPOINTMENT ONLY." A red light bulb above the frame, currently on.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c8f31489-3789-474b-8e7f-d5df3b48bc3b">
      <Text>She tries the door. It opens.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="0d8d74ea-20f3-49c1-b71c-98bbb6fc3962">
      <Text>A narrow reception area. Fake orchids. A bead curtain. A MADAM behind a counter— 60s, reading glasses, watching a Korean drama on an iPad propped against a tissue box. She looks up at Jaz without alarm.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ac6890d9-b0fc-4dde-ad95-63eaa208d00a">
      <Text>Behind the bead curtain: a hallway of closed doors. Muffled music. The specific silence of rooms where people are pretending not to hear each other.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="31f865a7-d782-4fed-a21e-4f5e4a87149d">
      <Text>MADAM</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="e925952e-2209-4606-8478-ad6022a5de0f">
      <Text>(flat, not pausing the drama)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="309abadf-54f5-49d8-846d-3c291e7a5d32">
      <Text>No appointment, no service.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="9b3cde25-8cf4-46c3-b385-898c07b2334e">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="e24879a5-eddf-4cd9-a847-332ac76e5f00">
      <Text>(scanning for exits)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="4b40e468-b76c-489c-8455-0a169350dab2">
      <Text>I don't need a service. I need your fire escape.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="bc18e2de-9c78-47b7-9456-62f2a9f6a7d1">
      <Text>MADAM</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b942492e-9fe0-44f9-a5a1-b801d7613433">
      <Text>Fire escape is for employees.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f221b2d2-38e4-4767-9fcd-80ea690010bf">
      <Text>A door at the end of the hallway opens. A middle-aged MAN in a polo shirt steps out, not making eye contact with anyone, tucking his shirt in, moving fast toward the exit. A WOMAN in a silk robe leans in the doorway behind him, bored, scrolling her phone.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8ebaf030-d8a8-49ef-abb0-e839fe4a6706">
      <Text>Knock Offs on the stairwell below. Getting closer.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="492c7ae6-89d6-4fee-a2c9-d7dbc2502c27">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="d16ea2e2-ce10-48e0-9dbb-081c943037e6">
      <Text>(pulling a hundred from the messenger bag, slapping it on the counter)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e45131f0-3f43-432c-935a-a1f7b9da0db3">
      <Text>I'm an employee.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="96c40a2a-0f9c-4e8b-a9e9-833e3650f933">
      <Text>The Madam looks at the hundred. Looks at Jaz. Looks at the stairwell door. She has been in this neighborhood long enough to know what Knockoffs on stairs means.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f42279b5-92dd-4a4a-bae6-9d755bb38dab">
      <Text>She hits a buzzer under the counter. The door at the end of the hallway clicks open. Behind it: a back room. Massage tables. Towels. A window with a fire escape.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="e5df8c6c-3b41-4410-a007-c69f62e8eb7f">
      <Text>MADAM</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="df94a249-d98f-47fd-9a35-51ae89bbc106">
      <Text>(eyes back on the iPad)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="06be2d8f-a0a7-4cdf-9e78-1f679752a800">
      <Text>Out the window. Close it behind you. You were never here.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ec7d9780-e1d7-485b-bfac-deba623e9723">
      <Text>Jaz is through the bead curtain, down the hall, past two closed doors and whatever's happening behind them, through the back room, and out the window in six seconds.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="3552a8a4-397f-4134-ac37-83b7e1ab05c5">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="31" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. FIRE ESCAPE - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b85211d6-24b0-44a1-8674-f5bda8ab2369">
      <Text>Rusted iron. The bolts probably haven't been inspected since the Clinton administration. The whole structure groans when she hits it.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="bad27ba8-5771-4e10-b35d-c499fc496a3e">
      <Text>She goes UP. Not down. Down is where they expect her. Up is the roof.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c570aebe-d6d5-4ba6-bf29-8f14e05ced0f">
      <Text>One flight. Two. The fire escape swaying slightly away from the building. Her hands on the railing, rust flaking under her grip. She can see down into the alley— Guy #2 is below, looking up, trying to figure out which window she came from.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="07a9fa6d-1a5e-4277-92e1-6eeee6bedb5a">
      <Text>She hits the roof.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="cebe8f60-f939-494a-ad16-eea6e9dc39ce">
      <SceneProperties Length="4/8" Page="31" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. ROOFTOP - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7abb7574-d039-4931-afc1-9b586610d81b">
      <Text>Tar and gravel. Water tanks. Satellite dishes. A pigeon coop that someone still maintains— the birds startling as she runs past, exploding into the air in a gray-white cloud.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9f8688b1-0b79-4ba0-a527-88f1d6560aa5">
      <Text>She crosses the roof. Doesn't stop. The next building is three feet away and two feet lower. She jumps. Lands hard. Rolls. Gravel in her palms. Keeps going.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="37d762fc-8f6d-408c-b8f7-b493bb6cf811">
      <Text>Second rooftop. She can hear Guy #2 on the fire escape below. The iron clanging.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e47fd6a9-46c6-4bcf-99d6-162359ad8ec3">
      <Text>She finds a roof access door. Pulls it. Locked. FUCK. Another one on the far side. Pulls it.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d73a76ba-3e3c-40e8-bc2b-1ce10d8f4496">
      <Text>Open.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c9f80bb1-0081-41c9-b153-245250082861">
      <Text>She's in another stairwell. Going down now. Fast. Holding the railing, swinging around each landing. The bag hammering her ribs with every turn.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8e6ea872-8c38-4c90-8f01-a0a6b2916a07">
      <Text>She comes out on the ground floor. A hallway. A door to the street. She slows. Catches her breath. Pushes the door open—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="4b8549d0-7c1c-469c-b6db-ecebc4873437">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="32" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. ELIZABETH STREET - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4d832137-7651-4853-8374-c1d0913602e6">
      <Text>Different block. She's come out a full block east of where she went in. She steps onto the sidewalk. Tries to walk. Tries to be a girl walking.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="20ed0e2b-8fd2-45dd-afd3-d15948f9d202">
      <Text>Her heart is slamming. Sweat on her temples. Her hands shaking from the fire escape rust and the adrenaline.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1afff532-6fbc-4f34-b439-aa206c97c8ac">
      <Text>She walks to the corner. Raises her hand. A cab pulls over.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="1da9bd82-6210-4bde-a1f5-5877101ad7e7">
      <SceneProperties Length="1" Page="32" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CABBIE">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAZ">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. CAB - CHINATOWN - CONTINUOUS</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="867162e5-24b9-40e7-b5f8-415cf1fe5c62">
      <Text>JAZ slides into the back seat. The door isn't closed before—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="88a61af0-215c-4e56-8658-46680dcac47d">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="2c009082-d85e-4571-8bb4-e57a7a440db3">
      <Text>150 William. Fast.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d84b3de0-8edb-415d-9d67-742126b6779b">
      <Text>The CABBIE pulls from the curb.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="88fdf9d7-86d5-4363-bdfb-81516228edcd">
      <Text>Jaz pulls out her phone. Opens Signal. Types:</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="895d0171-d07b-4e53-bcfb-d7ff1945c4dd">
      <Text>JAZ: on my way. 15 min. chips cashed. have the lease.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a417d1dd-1122-43e4-9ec6-15e3670221e5">
      <Text>Three dots.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="fc61f8a8-6a30-4940-92ef-34b79d397f90">
      <Text>HUNTER: </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">im</Text>
      <Text> here. bring coffee. this place is hell.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="077b020b-0a2f-4fec-adda-9c64adb266e9">
      <Text>She pockets the phone. Leans back. Breathes.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7c767f7b-b466-4d88-9944-761e20ccc292">
      <Text>Her hands are shaking. Just slightly. She puts them in her lap and presses them together until they stop.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="199794f0-de20-4e4a-9a7f-329f06c6e9f8">
      <Text>It's the image of Tanner's hand. The gauze. The shape where the finger should be.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="534f663a-af08-409f-9111-516d18a12e6f">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="512f3895-147a-4d76-be6f-86ab54dd2b49">
      <Text>They took his fucking finger-</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2f984c75-422d-4488-9bfc-cd55d7ff46a0">
      <Text>She looks out the rear window again. He's there just a speck now. Desperation radiating from every motion still looking for her. Then nothing. Gone behind a produce truck.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="fd73c291-b23f-4906-8b5d-cf4a47058143">
      <Text>CABBIE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="45b79af5-bbfe-40f0-a0b1-f65a956cb122">
      <Text>Sorry Ma'am?..</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c04e8590-04e1-499e-8a7e-d16878d708e5">
      <Text>The cab turns north on Bowery. She faces forward.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="05a7d858-166c-4179-855e-b87b78cd3b14">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="b83ceb17-ce18-49ef-a4b9-ea59154f5162">
      <Text>(to the cabbie)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="3984aaa4-b710-4723-9b2d-08abfe6d3ead">
      <Text>Uh, nothing... Can you go faster.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="41c92fc3-c957-43c0-a0ea-bba6ef7e5e62">
      <Text>CABBIE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="fd08e3d7-a0fb-431d-ba46-46fc268db555">
      <Text>It's Manhattan.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="b83b0f89-c6af-4ca3-ab7c-aa49e24f48b5">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="70ad3d89-155b-4a78-a820-3da200018e7d">
      <Text>Yeah.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="41467435-85e6-4c36-84b5-7f44d580b8a8">
      <Text>She watches the city slide past. </Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d4732ebd-d8a9-4066-bb35-fd4b00d3d78a">
      <Text>She's going to get her brother.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="3cea327e-e4ab-4a74-9957-e2599399c646">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 3/8" Page="33" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HUNTER">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="INTAKE CLERK">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. ACS MANHATTAN FIELD OFFICE - FRONT DESK - MORNING</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f2e431a4-e2e7-419e-b06b-0e7ef3b5b809">
      <Text>HUNTER is losing a war.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2de46893-3de2-49ca-a8ed-41b11de4ac55">
      <Text>The INTAKE CLERK sits behind bulletproof glass with a computer from 2011 and the expression of a person who has heard every version of every story and believes none of them.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c625bbab-52ab-4358-ba0d-c24b0d15ca16">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="809f6534-9ecb-4362-98e1-8d66df789a3c">
      <Text>—retained as counsel for the McCort family as of this morning. I am formally notifying this office that I represent Jamie McCort, a minor currently in your custody, and that his adult sibling is en route to file for emergency kinship placement.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="489b7f06-1de0-4152-9d4e-2b21e82137ea">
      <Text>INTAKE CLERK</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="d862ec3b-0eb4-492c-940f-6298d47f6ab8">
      <Text>(looking at the screen)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="77fe5313-c7b3-48b1-ba83-b37808b812bc">
      <Text>I don't have any record of that in the computer.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a245dee5-b189-4554-b26a-214126e5f325">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a0a5740d-7f05-4421-9cc2-659ba862d571">
      <Text>Right. Because I'm telling you now. So you can put it in the computer.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="2afbe762-3ffa-449d-b976-ebb90184475d">
      <Text>INTAKE CLERK</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b123cd95-0284-4e4c-899f-b3f8a4a1b0c2">
      <Text>I can't put it in the computer until I have documentation.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="1a8804e7-7581-40b3-a1e1-fc27fd621552">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="44ccb975-aa84-4c26-8e06-97b0c3f9ac9f">
      <Text>I am the documentation. I'm his attorney. I'm standing here. Documenting.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="46c0009b-6a29-4ddf-b226-417d3389e14a">
      <Text>INTAKE CLERK</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="4569859a-46be-4d62-bc17-cbfaf34870fb">
      <Text>Do you have a retainer agreement?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="fde26466-0783-456d-8b2b-0ca095819a43">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f7fc23e2-ac9a-4b7a-aa22-d8832749fcb8">
      <Text>It's being formalized.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ad5c1113-491f-40be-9d07-c9ac1dcf4be7">
      <Text>INTAKE CLERK</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="be0838ac-49e4-4f5b-acec-96724e5fe85a">
      <Text>So you don't have documentation.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="8cc8a0e7-b093-43de-afd7-437ed614f35c">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="297e21cc-e98e-4f56-b0b4-f4ab4dc869d2">
      <Text>I have a bar card.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="2fab2fa9-9818-414e-9749-a431e14452f3">
      <Text>INTAKE CLERK</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="871a720f-9dc0-4172-b557-def867d094b6">
      <Text>I need a retainer agreement, a signed authorization from a parent or legal guardian, and a case number.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ef035ebf-0083-4a1c-92d3-9a64d99794d3">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a3b9f848-f718-420d-9e13-0a3318342dbd">
      <Text>Both parents are in custody. That's why the child is HERE.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7981b60e-7a5b-4553-b565-00965b16134e">
      <Text>Hunter puts both hands on the counter. Breathes. The hangover is still there. The Folgers' benefit is since gone.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f59aa829-162d-4817-a777-0732e0a5a36c">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="cef11bf4-a6cf-4058-8b88-9dda39e71e6a">
      <Text>Can I speak to a supervisor?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="2f19ee57-acf1-4891-9b7b-63c94040b02c">
      <Text>INTAKE CLERK</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="84f608c1-c794-4047-b6cc-482cb49b9f2b">
      <Text>She's at lunch.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="efb1b3ce-4c0f-462b-90e5-f75266a96ae4">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="7d96960b-542b-4cb5-851b-7395cd240cf0">
      <Text>It's nine-thirty in the morning.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4d9423db-5a2b-401d-af23-44d0b3400895">
      <Text>INTAKE CLERK</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="cb1a9fef-1cfd-4e78-8428-3c38bc8552f5">
      <Text>She eats early.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="808dae02-3c9a-4ca4-ad44-2def232c392b">
      <SceneProperties Length="2 6/8" Page="34" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HUNTER">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="INTAKE CLERK">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAMIE">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAZ">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. ACS - HALLWAY - SAME TIME</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2ebb9322-6b89-4873-9045-10a4f8bd85f3">
      <Text>JAMIE heard the commotion two minutes ago. Not the words— the rhythm. The specific cadence of someone arguing with a bureaucracy and losing.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d88b6153-b345-4588-9278-005b8daa8074">
      <Text>He stands. Leaves the waiting area. Nobody stops him. Nobody notices. He is fourteen and barefoot and completely invisible to every adult in this building.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e5aae9b5-5dd9-4435-bf63-ae17b4f72675">
      <Text>He walks down the hall toward the front desk. Fluorescent lights buzz overhead. Posters about hand-washing. A water fountain that doesn't work.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b5628a72-149b-446d-82ce-45a3a69773f2">
      <Text>Two CHILD ADVOCATES come through a side door hauling a pair of KIDS— maybe ten, maybe twelve— who are kicking and screaming and biting and doing everything in their power to not be where they are. One kid catches an advocate in the shin. The advocate doesn't flinch. Tuesday.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="01280863-052a-461d-beeb-4f3454509622">
      <Text>Jamie walks past them like he's passing weather. The kids scream. The advocates wrestle. Jamie keeps walking. Barefoot.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="General" id="c0d11b53-35ed-48a5-bcea-73595c69d6c5">
      <Text>Hoodie. Hands in his pockets. A ghost in the machine.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d86ac5bd-f49e-40d6-8045-ccdfd93f0b42">
      <Text>He rounds the corner to the front desk. Sees Hunter. Doesn't recognize him.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="47245ad8-0281-4a4d-905d-d3a9d36a745d">
      <Text>He stops. Stands there. Watching Hunter argue with a clerk about a computer that won't accept reality.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="1d64b33b-bbfa-420a-8e01-0de6bf6c88db">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="9c0b4b4a-82ee-44cf-a5c6-8e9e0367ead0">
      <Text>—if you would just let me explain one more time— Jamie McCort.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="b4f209cb-3f3a-44fd-ab95-c0401d911b6b">
      <Text>INTAKE CLERK</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a80c95fc-23f9-47f6-ba67-42101dbcc7c6">
      <Text>Sir, without documentation—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b3e7569b-12d3-4180-8d80-df79453bd853">
      <Text>The front door BANGS open.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="90d90309-8a6a-4db4-945f-014d63a948a5">
      <Text>JAZ.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7ffeb443-5441-4829-961d-09f7ab621356">
      <Text>Ramones shirt. Combat boots. Messenger bag. That leather she treats like her second skin. She is breathing hard. She ran from the cab.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="88771e08-b2cc-425b-95c3-de0af7186eb4">
      <Text>She sees the desk. She sees Hunter. She sees the clerk. And then she sees, standing ten feet down the hall, barefoot on the linoleum—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="d401d8c2-4db9-4f89-8852-9b6a1221923a">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="334e9992-4a43-4ca3-a5d3-ceacf5b061e9">
      <Text>JAMIE.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="05a1e00a-9b70-49f2-a573-b26cb98103de">
      <Text>Jamie turns.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ffc88801-8b78-48d6-979c-40991ef9ad94">
      <Text>She is across the lobby in three steps. The messenger bag swings wide and hits a chair. She doesn't care. She grabs him. Both arms. Pulls him into her so hard his feet leave the floor for a second.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f477d84d-0925-4290-ae16-c94a032f302f">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="9c4d748b-f32c-48b0-a954-da03f3a4f173">
      <Text>(into his shoulder, breaking)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="5929e8e6-8b17-44a6-9be3-22bb38a83e3d">
      <Text>I'm sorry. I'm so sorry. I wasn't there. I should have been there. I'm sorry.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3c71960b-f115-4110-8548-a128ae4f2075">
      <Text>Jamie stands in her arms. He's fine. He doesn't know why, exactly. But his hands come up. Slowly. And he holds her back.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="8f141554-db9f-4053-b5ca-1a103180458b">
      <Text>JAMIE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="94685aee-8fca-45b6-abb8-44c70bf6fdf0">
      <Text>(quiet, factual)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="9ee4fa27-ed0c-41ea-a08c-9c3ccda6424f">
      <Text>I'm fine, Jaz.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c441db69-d74f-4ec9-8e0d-8c382beb4ee8">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="79956f6f-1607-4080-a5b0-ca8ded8386ce">
      <Text>(still holding him, crying)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="236252b0-e1f0-4805-afcd-7130236d4630">
      <Text>You don't have shoes.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="28427289-4262-40d1-9a0d-b4eb103553a6">
      <Text>JAMIE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b5891d7e-2da0-4307-9678-44bf18319caa">
      <Text>They said they'd get me shoes. They didn't.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="55f39ad1-22f4-434c-bdf7-82ed9859a8b7">
      <Text>She pulls back. Holds his face in both hands. Looks at him. Studies him the way she studies everything— reading the tells, looking for damage.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a9f5ce94-0b49-4259-991e-44e97e7450cb">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="fe0373bf-ce63-4df8-8ddc-d724b1022221">
      <Text>Are you okay. Are you actually okay.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="d72e832f-6f8a-4f6b-99fa-e169cc3bbea0">
      <Text>JAMIE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="450f8677-90a7-427a-9c64-7a0db8d8c183">
      <Text>I'm fine. I've been sitting in a chair drinking a juice box. It wasn't good juice.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d56ce476-60b7-4ee4-9c2f-b5234e58f914">
      <Text>She laughs. A broken, wet laugh. Wipes her face with the back of her hand.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="49b7c126-57ae-46fc-a0a9-7e1a5f444d6c">
      <Text>Hunter watches from the counter. The clerk watches from behind the glass. Even the clerk's expression has shifted— just barely, just a crack in the bureaucratic armor.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f81f8ed9-ea17-4ca2-8a1a-72ab9b4d18d4">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="bcafde4a-a4c5-4752-8151-d6384593a0b5">
      <Text>(to the clerk, quiet)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b271b4c8-432b-4745-8c35-ce914817e647">
      <Text>That's the sister.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="0d3a5388-b3d5-4ea4-a1e5-8bd1c92bf567">
      <Text>The clerk looks at Jaz. Looks at Jamie. Looks at the computer.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ac0d1117-5766-4ed9-b55b-4ff98716b093">
      <Text>Types something.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="26f6ec82-9a56-44cb-a796-f66a1bc03417">
      <Text>INTAKE CLERK</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="856e65e3-b442-46ed-b3ae-83c3ddf9adc7">
      <Text>I'm going to need her ID.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4bf26ef0-3b99-454d-af9b-0cf065531c1a">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="2117c70b-6c04-4c87-b764-dbfbe71a8f1c">
      <Text>(stops, recalibrates)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="17119f96-8448-4e39-bdfd-29b7071c4f24">
      <Text>She'll have documentation. Give us ten minutes.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f31e6438-bbd5-4a1c-8ca3-45695f562825">
      <Text>He turns to Jaz. She's still holding Jamie's face. Still looking at him like she's confirming he's real.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="e1baa022-d93d-45e2-bbad-995357ddbc3a">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="deb71612-9602-4dae-8cd6-76be69f1fdfe">
      <Text>(gentle)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="5c91960a-f564-4621-aac7-6aff987df9ec">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">Phe</Text>
      <Text>- Uh- Jaz. We need to talk to them. You have the lease?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ef7bc24d-9536-4a84-bedd-c2ff0c778386">
      <Text>She nods. Wipes her eyes. Reaches into the bag.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d20aa470-dab2-4a52-93f1-2ac1ebfb49d9">
      <Text>Jamie looks at Hunter. Then at Jaz. Then at Hunter again.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ae85daa6-26c2-42c3-9c40-1177e7e0b261">
      <Text>JAMIE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="06502ff6-be1b-4a75-b077-576a5d44c684">
      <Text>(to Jaz)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="021e5083-2243-45be-bd6b-c76c77baf0dc">
      <Text>Is that one of your poker guys?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="3a4ea664-b178-46eb-bc38-67d5918bd1ef">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="368fbcd7-4a81-4a3e-8ad3-b7f4d999aa70">
      <Text>(sniffing, pulling out the lease)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="5d97f3fc-45b0-46b6-a37d-03b28a63cafc">
      <Text>He's our lawyer.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="047ad04f-f212-455f-beb6-bef0fe56069a">
      <Text>Jamie looks at Hunter. The wrinkled shirt. The hangover.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="9ddbff7e-3d2d-431d-83fd-e6b8caa5a46d">
      <Text>JAMIE</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="bd2eadc8-4a8b-4651-9a7c-8c43e9818bfa">
      <Text>We're fucked.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="edfa89e6-03a0-4fec-9f52-261aad171159">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="03aa4076-26b1-4eb6-87ba-d39e05767263">
      <Text>I get that a lot.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="fc9f8442-04a5-4ff2-92bc-adfe74ed21c1">
      <SceneProperties Length="5 3/8" Page="37" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HUNTER">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEVIN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="SARAH">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. CENTRAL BOOKING - INTERVIEW ROOM - AFTERNOON</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d8f4c6fe-6dd8-4770-bd2e-9b6a8739342b">
      <Text>A room the size of a parking space. Metal table bolted to the floor. Two chairs. One fluorescent tube buzzing overhead like it's considering retirement.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a946afa3-b189-4c40-b939-2b24a8976cdd">
      <Text>KEVIN sits on one side.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="226b55b0-1b3a-4aa1-9435-920f81f83aa7">
      <Text>Across from him: SARAH FRANKS (30s), Legal Aid Society. Organized. Competent. A stack of files under one arm because she has nine other arraignments today and Kevin McCort is number six.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b2acf6ca-7756-4220-86e4-c66071643051">
      <Text>She has a legal pad open. A pen ready.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="03e68d9c-26b4-4bb3-ad4a-a6634e6a344c">
      <Text>SARAH</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="d9e24150-e8d3-4f6e-869a-b753e82ade6f">
      <Text>Mr. McCort, I've reviewed the complaint. I want to walk you through the charges and discuss—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="e1524f3a-6023-4736-94ae-b369c82266e4">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e0f6122c-ebdd-499d-8a81-71eaa3140548">
      <Text>I had the best attorneys this morning. All the top firms. And not one of them can represent me because they all work for MY company. The company I BUILT.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f7c2b118-6074-4f98-a1d8-83e5efa1585a">
      <Text>He stops. Breathes. Looks at her.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="af11806d-fddc-49eb-a309-a89a7109754c">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="7254482e-32c7-49ec-9b9d-195f48b7187e">
      <Text>I'm not— this isn't about you. You seem very capable. I'm sure you're very good at what you do, and you have your reasons for not being at a respectable firm.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="6f34136e-216a-4a16-8b2c-092d6afa9b1b">
      <Text>SARAH</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="d7c68414-57ac-4f80-b560-c1801d217def">
      <Text>I am, and I do.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ae8e4aa6-d5a5-47a1-8b68-ab1154fd8947">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="d0159940-349e-41db-8b95-6c393cdc616c">
      <Text>It's just that yesterday I had Chet Masters on speed dial and today I'm—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="435f8afd-5ce7-42e4-87aa-007df56adfa5">
      <Text>He gestures at the room. At her. At everything.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a95b00a4-2bff-40f9-b57c-b808dc77ef48">
      <Text>SARAH</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="ddaa81b3-e5b8-45ff-b0c9-ebdf7d28c241">
      <Text>In a room with a public defender.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d825f03d-660d-405b-a9b8-756d92e5e802">
      <Text>The door opens.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="fd055c0b-37f3-4f08-85a2-b757c01ec4ff">
      <Text>HUNTER REID in full glory.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9a26904f-e81d-4128-89cd-d3e7aaa37edc">
      <Text>Wrinkled white shirt, one button still wrong. The jacket that has been to places jackets shouldn't go. Hair that has been wet and has since dried into a shape that suggests a weather event. A faint Folgers stain on his chest that he hasn't noticed or has decided to live with.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5f94cbde-4f65-40dd-ade1-26b67d4880ba">
      <Text>He is carrying a yellow legal pad, a pen, and the specific energy of a man running on cold instant coffee and adrenaline.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="b87ebf33-7f12-40a9-9d0a-87614e79a6e3">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="6af5717d-9e41-4c3d-b911-a9c647527721">
      <Text>Sorry to interrupt. Hunter Reid, attorney at law. I've been retained to represent Mr. McCort. My advice to my client is to shut the fuck up.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="636b0af0-72e7-429a-9885-1ad5688c9748">
      <Text>Kevin stares at him.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c0c15949-e709-4c1e-8fd2-4b2fc8384258">
      <Text>Sarah stares at him.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ea42f010-fb8f-4b3a-9426-7a5dc9f15c9b">
      <Text>SARAH</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="9db2d29d-83b2-45b0-8afb-665ee1cd8279">
      <Text>Retained by whom?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c0249916-9714-44d8-b114-91d0650672d1">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="85d2d06a-5fc4-408f-a9d2-f0802b816ae7">
      <Text>By his daughter. Jazmine McCort. She's eighteen. She has standing.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4e343104-bc5f-4f9b-add4-107054bcc021">
      <Text>Hunter reaches into his jacket. Pulls out a folded piece of paper. It is, like everything else that has been printed on the card table in the St. Marks basement today, slightly stained and warm from his body heat.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e22aaf1e-c0c3-4a2a-b76e-79138df6f351">
      <Text>He unfolds it. Sets it on the metal table.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="8bda6e8a-a56a-4614-98bb-a8765b60b412">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="abca5a2c-f4de-4b59-92fc-fa019421a0ac">
      <Text>Signed this morning.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9069c881-dbca-44b7-add8-065d9edc497d">
      <Text>Sarah picks it up. Reads it. It's legitimate—barely. Boilerplate language. Two signatures. Dated today.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a3e056ab-c9ba-466a-8670-ff7dc95ea01d">
      <Text>SARAH</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="722d491e-25f7-4a07-8436-4f86d8564fca">
      <Text>Alright He was my 6th this morning and I have 3 more. He's yours.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="0f8f7675-a137-4f54-805a-3d06fb61bb8b">
      <Text>She gathers her files. Stands. Pauses at the door.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="b01d27b3-10d0-4396-8218-5fa481b3a923">
      <Text>SARAH</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="a594c99f-d536-43e7-b3c6-cbc560c89310">
      <Text>(to Kevin)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="989c8b3e-cac0-451a-93fb-1ce0ddf6fb7f">
      <Text>Good luck, Mr. McCort.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6af7403a-a4d3-47a9-89f7-458beefa889d">
      <Text>She's gone. Kevin looks at Hunter. Takes in the full picture. The shirt. The jacket. The hair. The stain. The yellow legal pad that appears to have pad </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">thai</Text>
      <Text> grease on the corner.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="075fe4b2-7d31-4e21-b9d1-c7e9e1cf42c3">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="6104856e-1d00-4133-80a8-1241937b06ae">
      <Text>My daughter sent you.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a55dcc2c-8cd2-4167-bcae-8d565ff500c1">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="ecbfcd25-3394-4bb3-a02f-df31908bacce">
      <Text>Yes.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="10cbbee5-70c4-4e4d-a0c3-dc62d6197ced">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="ea6b7f54-2728-45aa-9625-9833b0314f93">
      <Text>You're an attorney.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="6d91877b-e07f-4720-aaa9-64a12815362e">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="2ec8d864-b473-4714-83f1-8d329ba2fe8d">
      <Text>Yes.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ade3c8d1-dc29-4112-867a-3bf2b3eb9aeb">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="eba85ba3-6439-4bf9-8c7a-fb35bfa70a6b">
      <Text>Where did you go to school?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="01e7ccc7-85cf-402a-b0bc-d3c3654bf1ad">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="0615452a-5ba5-41c4-981c-b24844998944">
      <Text>Columbia.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c88a3060-da35-44f2-acb3-bc679b1d86e0">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="2e9bbad1-ed89-4be7-9a3c-d2b96f3970e9">
      <Text>(a flicker of hope)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e42d46a1-4363-4eb7-9856-6b468896f96c">
      <Text>Columbia.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="b9ebd439-b0b0-420f-bf5e-6159266ad79a">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="41241ec5-0398-4f70-862f-aa674b644948">
      <Text>Bottom third.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2afcf708-3111-40e1-baa9-bf369c36fbd1">
      <Text>The flicker dies.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c9637f9a-0682-41ba-81a1-381f5c558e99">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="443250b0-6caa-49e9-9571-d1ccc9e040dc">
      <Text>And your firm?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="b9327e3a-c6f4-4ad7-b323-124b942dfd32">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="5e57866b-9f38-40f7-baa5-210bb9ff2512">
      <Text>I'm independent.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="299445f9-6dd0-45ea-9655-3a5abfc4250b">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="3fafda02-a786-4258-bd0a-004b8d5f0855">
      <Text>Independent.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="10e40d56-314b-4f62-b732-324f9c223884">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="df09245d-488b-4b7c-b8e5-712bceca8e66">
      <Text>Solo practice.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="9d13dfb7-b8d9-4fc1-9912-dd2bd5a4097b">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="7755f616-a40f-4099-80d6-66e562797950">
      <Text>Where is your office?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="11abbdd4-4483-4d95-b48b-e39c7a3dce45">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="dc874cb7-bc60-4a99-8995-4013f8682cdc">
      <Text>(a beat too long)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="4b7c4b82-98d6-4ca0-835e-39eb2d90100e">
      <Text>St. Marks Place.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1cdf54f2-7676-4400-85fc-6e030ba9d2a2">
      <Text>Kevin looks at the door Sarah just walked through. Then</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="General" id="9abc2635-e833-44d2-80d7-8d3745fef246">
      <Text>back at Hunter. The public defender— organized, competent— versus this man, who appears to have slept in his clothes and may not have slept at all.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="1ef72aac-738d-475b-8a1f-2374de47f072">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="6d9ac9a6-4af7-491f-918b-31da57c75903">
      <Text>How much is my daughter paying you?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="08a4f062-fbb2-4590-aa4c-4232ddad9c6e">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="e282be42-39d3-4a6d-bcfb-8e5531f505e6">
      <Text>Enough.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="1a7a2770-6e39-4b12-8afd-8e5ee985bb13">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="fe91c0b3-7048-466d-9a29-8dce2fea0c76">
      <Text>And your experience with securities fraud?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="38fc7b61-803f-4be7-bcea-8a183efe7fd8">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="c1322556-cd32-418b-9e0d-350a1a2275e1">
      <Text>I'm a fast reader.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9d6c841b-a0f8-44c1-bf8c-689fe6cf6fbe">
      <Text>Kevin puts his head in his hands. The ink on his fingers presses into his forehead. When he looks up, he'll have smudges above his eyebrows and won't know for hours.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="6fc5f0dd-cce2-4ac1-9d4c-b36fdda5ce03">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="327e0e70-5083-4c99-8682-ce5555a29b69">
      <Text>What's your advice.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="5b6f2bc5-1985-4a77-b1bf-0f44011b119f">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="cf9959c1-305b-4a54-9ec8-c791acca3a8c">
      <Text>(sitting down, opening the legal pad, clicking the pen)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="0a6ed218-6ef3-4ed3-97de-778f9bd9bc60">
      <Text>I already gave it. Shut the fuck up. Don't say another word to anyone who isn't me.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="7411960e-6176-4b01-bd8b-6f3393d22260">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="c4772956-e3d6-4c6f-a847-a25415727fa6">
      <Text>I wasn't going to—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="138cca71-9359-4237-b488-62be0c96ce81">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="465bb648-7fc7-4baf-84f8-e5897ba6af61">
      <Text>You've been talking since the cuffs went on. I can tell. You have the face of a man who's been explaining himself to every person you see regardless of who's listening.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7315554e-6e0d-432b-8c28-7a602f217eeb">
      <Text>Kevin opens his mouth. Closes it.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4000c990-fd0e-4780-9e07-69ee44dcf2de">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="ae78df88-f908-4e4d-9b5f-fefc0606ff00">
      <Text>That. That right there. Whatever you were about to say? Don't. That's the whole strategy for the next forty-five minutes. We go in front of the judge. We enter not guilty. We argue bail. And you say nothing except "not guilty" and "yes, Your Honor." Can you do that?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="79537ca0-3c12-4355-baea-8a0d7b565808">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="b39a5532-5263-4419-b154-54d11f498072">
      <Text>(measuring him)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="50595a58-dc8a-45f0-8d62-5d4b61bb44f6">
      <Text>Can you get me out of here?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="3d45458c-458e-4ba4-bfd5-6618fd741f10">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="113a2d2e-05e1-41dd-867d-880f3e296c9f">
      <Text>I'm going to try very hard.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="7ff87692-6f3a-496d-bc40-9d51fb1d167b">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="7541374f-5c29-4108-8cfd-0da4fa443ff3">
      <Text>That's it? This is ridiculous. My daughter is a child and couldn't possibly understand what's at stake here, much less be able to vet a competent defense attorney.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f4e155b8-7e3b-4e63-93a6-f09ea9386eed">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="0b897b25-6df2-4d37-89c3-68e83cc3533a">
      <Text>Mr. McCort, twelve hours ago I saw your daughter win north of a quarter million dollars in a poker game in Chinatown. Six hours ago she was standing on a sidewalk watching your wife get put in a squad car. Three hours ago she was in my apartment. She's been to Chinatown, to the Lower East Side, to ACS where she pulled your son out of the system, and now she's upstairs in the gallery waiting for your arraignment. She hasn't slept. She hasn't eaten. And she paid me and sent me down here to get your wife out and make sure you don't talk yourself into a prison sentence.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c538e693-4add-49f3-b9da-d8e016386f1d">
      <Text>He leans forward.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="99408978-08c1-4c34-9d8f-970139d5e9f1">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="9be81f70-86be-43d8-a62c-564ed2ccda21">
      <Text>That's all I know, other than she believes you are innocent.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="fe1678ac-1ec0-4944-86df-1d120d109002">
      <Text>(beat)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="24d96d1a-269a-4670-add4-2760f148397a">
      <Text>I may not be what you're used to. But I'm what showed up, and to be completely honest, I showed up for her. Not you.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d157fb30-77da-4208-b7dc-90872264ff80">
      <Text>Kevin looks at him. A long beat. The fluorescent tube buzzes.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a4f9347f-34f4-4a1e-a62c-68f24222b43e">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f563cb7a-71c6-4096-8ec1-869de0d93f0d">
      <Text>Up to you, man. We doing this or not?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ed2422e1-0943-4088-b7de-b25d4173421d">
      <Text>Somewhere in Kevin McCort's brain, maybe its the new setting, maybe the weather, who knows, but a small window of understanding cracks just open enough to have something new stick.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a727f8dd-910c-4f5f-a6ca-597cd56958c2">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="b8525478-120b-4125-b885-d1911557bb52">
      <Text>(quiet)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="16f93414-08fa-4a53-9c6d-060dd8faac38">
      <Text>She got Jamie out?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="72689996-cdee-4e98-b8c1-07b2bb4caa67">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="42a66fcb-b234-452a-a8c7-12f9f08a7b79">
      <Text>He's upstairs. With her. He's fine. He's got shoes now.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c4dfbc97-d9a6-46ef-8d0a-9edec5bfb190">
      <Text>Something in Kevin's face breaks. Just for a second. Just enough.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4e3c00aa-3d05-485c-96e9-0211ed9235bb">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="0038533a-c9b6-486a-9e37-d47c3c9e1d98">
      <Text>Okay.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="7383ce82-aba8-4411-afd1-ebca4ab0e3ed">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="1f3e0c3c-b02f-405e-b32e-c1de4f3cf90c">
      <Text>Okay?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4f585727-5ddb-4f86-8d93-17d72f4bdf5c">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="0ef088be-d701-4d67-ab2e-20b9cb5ccc30">
      <Text>Shut the fuck up. Not guilty. Yes, Your Honor.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="9d39431d-03df-43dd-9273-4d20163af1e7">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="f7384967-df03-4739-93b9-56ea68ea555c">
      <Text>(clicking the pen)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="c972dd4c-f192-46a5-b8d8-e7ed329ea408">
      <Text>Now you're getting it.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="cb849117-8d7f-419b-9953-1ce9a20ae877">
      <SceneProperties Length="3 3/8" Page="42" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ADA LIANG">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="COURT OFFICER">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HUNTER">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JUDGE KOLB">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEVIN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. MANHATTAN CRIMINAL COURT - ARRAIGNMENT - AFTERNOON</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5b2e42cf-fc67-4672-af68-1589057ea22b">
      <Text>The courtroom at 100 Centre is what happens when democracy meets fluorescent lighting. Wood paneling that was dignified in 1940. An American flag that needs steaming. A gallery of plastic chairs filled with the worried and the bored.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="502e5c79-6eab-45df-8f46-5514c064dc12">
      <Text>In the third row: JAZ, JAMIE, and JANET.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4816067e-16be-4ea1-84de-ca1e4ae463c3">
      <Text>Janet is back in the Lululemon. It's what she was arrested in. It's what she has. Over it, draped across her shoulders: Hunter's jacket. She's wearing it like a pashmina, which is the most Janet thing she could possibly do with a jacket that smells like Jameson and regret.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="bb700b32-b863-4cc2-85a2-25f3ab68c0ba">
      <Text>Jamie sits beside her. He has shoes now— cheap Nikes from a bodega, two sizes too big, laces untied. He's watching the proceedings with the focus of someone memorizing the system for future reference.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8460a664-1fa9-4f59-a7ff-d23cc6b73c31">
      <Text>Jaz sits on Janet's other side. Ramones tee. Hair dried into its natural shape. The shaved left side of her skull. The tattoo creeping up from behind her ear across her scalp. The septum ring.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="424a4265-ca74-47cd-9e88-2b3995b299ce">
      <Text>They have not discussed any of this. There has not been time.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="79c65376-f4fd-4b36-b87d-e7fccbbab6cd">
      <Text>A COURT OFFICER opens the side door.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="77d8b591-eebd-4566-905e-2abd294ddd77">
      <Text>COURT OFFICER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="0631fd99-f0c6-4489-8c3f-be6fabaa33b5">
      <Text>Docket number 2026-MN-047831. People versus Kevin McCort.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d59e8881-e8e6-45ba-88c1-44bbe865619c">
      <Text>Kevin walks in.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="03ca5fc2-311b-4808-b99d-a8e4b837ed75">
      <Text>He's been in the suit for too many hours. Shirt untucked on one side. Ink on his fingers and forehead from where he put his head in his hands. No watch. No ring. No tie.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e18329ee-0d2a-4304-b433-863d53fe7ee3">
      <Text>He scans the gallery.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="008291b7-104b-4bc8-a414-9f60daf849fa">
      <Text>He finds Janet first. The Lululemon. The jacket. She meets his eyes. Holds them. Gives nothing.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e6a925b6-22a9-456b-87c6-39306f2715b3">
      <Text>He finds Jamie. Small nod. Fine. Always fine.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="7ff83f11-1ec8-41c3-ae36-524a2ed17139">
      <Text>He finds Jaz.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c949b6ea-0693-4dae-9527-fdff8ac34127">
      <Text>He stops.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="83a77a1f-1a42-46e7-989e-438713530caf">
      <Text>Not physically— the court officer is guiding him forward— but something behind his eyes stops. Stalls. Reboots.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6b714fb2-0a1a-4e87-9d18-21e391ca3fb5">
      <Text>The face of his daughter without the Princeton mask she's been wearing in his presence for her whole life.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2e4566b8-2c59-4a70-a17e-808f097794b8">
      <Text>He looks at Janet— Still nothing.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="bf187bbf-684c-4c2c-92a4-7cd14194e1c2">
      <Text>He sits at the defense table. Hunter is already there.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="33d8fa07-2fb9-42d7-8caa-075927cbf22e">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="dae791fa-ac7a-4106-80c2-9272153f49e1">
      <Text>(leaning over, whispered)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b635f947-4722-41f0-9920-99d87497be89">
      <Text>What happened to her head?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="06b3e1d1-010f-4869-9bfc-2066115bd4b5">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="8a27d932-09e5-4e11-842d-c243c2f33406">
      <Text>(not looking up)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="ff41d39f-45af-45f3-ad23-2ba470648bff">
      <Text>Not now.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a0b08eff-2e80-4acc-81ec-cfb64d136c1a">
      <Text>The JUDGE—HONORABLE DIANE </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">KOLB</Text>
      <Text> (60s), reading glasses, ten thousand arraignments deep— reviews the file.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="03990881-d94b-401d-a517-4f3d58bea1f9">
      <Text>JUDGE </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">KOLB</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="1cb214fc-f024-43b6-8c56-ab28b68ed68a">
      <Text>Mr. McCort, you've been charged with violations of the Martin Act, securities fraud in the first degree, grand larceny in the first degree, money laundering in the second degree, and conspiracy in the fourth degree. How do you plead?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a7e992cb-437f-4c38-a5bc-935527e0c2fa">
      <Text>Kevin looks at Hunter. Hunter nods.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="004ea3e4-675f-4f36-93c7-215c3005087f">
      <Text>Kevin starts to stand. The COO instinct fires—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="513d341f-3424-4f9c-bfcc-840793acb4b9">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="eb1e3592-8729-411d-b9da-c31fae3471f5">
      <Text>Your Honor, I want to say—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e351073e-c54d-4596-bbfb-f6fdeae9932b">
      <Text>Hunter's hand on his forearm. Firm. Kevin looks over his shoulder at the family that looks so different than he knows.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="eca95f45-982c-4386-9480-e0d17234a44a">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="d9a901b5-a55f-4878-8be5-5bd24f62ad06">
      <Text>Um... uh. I mean. Not guilty, Your Honor.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="5584f81a-8f74-4141-8226-f03108adcc95">
      <Text>JUDGE </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">KOLB</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="86cd17f0-853b-4628-9f23-2bbeaad8d92f">
      <Text>People, on the matter of bail?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="55406873-761d-454b-8cd9-b23fa3c35546">
      <Text>ADA DIANA </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">LIANG</Text>
      <Text> (32), Chinese American, sharp, color-coded folders, stands.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="16943247-794a-4125-8836-50f0c782a4a7">
      <Text>ADA </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">LIANG</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="66fa6fc6-0a5e-4e21-8f3e-623bc007383d">
      <Text>The People request bail in the amount of five million dollars. Mr. McCort is charged with financial crimes exceeding sixty million dollars. He has substantial resources, international business connections, and the means and motive to flee. The People consider him a significant flight risk.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="bb4c2335-8f88-4c0b-ad70-dd4f5e60e69e">
      <Text>JUDGE </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">KOLB</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="6f16d611-8f8c-46c2-9564-11b2579b025c">
      <Text>Defense?</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="90590596-3191-43e0-b858-5850966becd9">
      <Text>Hunter stands. Buttons his jacket wrong. Doesn't notice.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="8cbcc34d-baeb-4a80-96cf-d49e201378f2">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="66ed83aa-79a3-43f4-83d9-fa42e6675da0">
      <Text>Your Honor, the People's characterization of my client's resources is fictional. As of seven this morning, every asset owned by Kevin and Janet McCort has been seized. Bank accounts frozen. Brokerage frozen. The family home seized and sealed. Mr. McCort couldn't buy a sandwich right now, let alone a plane ticket.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a6d5a960-7dc9-4a4f-a639-bd95938c0778">
      <Text>He doesn't need the legal pad. He's doing the thing.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="dd42f241-093b-4710-95ad-043affd0fab5">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="1eecb562-5eae-4e25-8ae3-95f6dd9e0c3b">
      <Text>As for flight risk— Mr. McCort has lived in Manhattan for twenty-two years. His children attend school in this city. His wife was arraigned in this courtroom two hours ago and released on conditions. The family's standing in the third row of your gallery, and their ties to the community run deep.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6a749006-e713-4c34-aa5d-437f7f6334a9">
      <Text>The judge looks. Jaz. Jamie. Janet. A family with nowhere to go.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c1a35c76-f5eb-455c-8e75-5dace2eef130">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="60eb3ce7-8d75-4a06-94bc-9ac378f6ffb2">
      <Text>My client will surrender his passport, which I might add is currently locked in a wall safe in the seized home. He will comply with any monitoring the court requires. The People's request is designed to ensure detention, not appearance.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="be60adb6-462c-4990-924f-6d8e3c3a0c91">
      <Text>She looks at Kevin. At the gallery. At Hunter with his wrong button.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="81c47519-b2b7-4485-af54-e90c02f87a98">
      <Text>JUDGE </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">KOLB</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f95de296-fa5a-462a-b12d-f053342b1fe4">
      <Text>Bail is set at two million five hundred thousand dollars. Passport surrender. Electronic monitoring. No contact with current or former employees of MedAnalytic Systems.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="41590561-2c00-49e6-8436-746c7834b3d7">
      <Text>Gavel. Next file.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="2f26a28b-0bf0-4aa7-869d-f1332fc51926">
      <Text>Kevin exhales.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="1ab2f3ba-445a-4c04-947a-1538bc44b174">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="d2b6a51d-c964-4d97-ade9-4899bd290e41">
      <Text>(whispered)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="0aaee83d-9b33-476d-a6ed-8d03f7960d71">
      <Text>Two and a half million.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="cd71756e-be21-4777-9bf1-203349eeff5f">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="324a0e09-4057-4292-b70b-cfbc0965d5f3">
      <Text>Partially secured bond. Ten percent. Two fifty.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="25ce677a-b4fb-4f6d-ac77-c05ff40469f8">
      <Text>Kevin is led to the side door. He looks back at the gallery. At Jaz. At the version of his daughter he's never seen. She holds his gaze and he can see it— maybe for the first time. The face that he's never seen before because she's never let him.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="f091d2ec-a452-406b-ad18-e36f070266fa">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 4/8" Page="46" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BAIL CLERK">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HUNTER">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAZ">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. CENTRAL BOOKING - BAIL WINDOW - MINUTES LATER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6356436c-95f2-4e36-911a-dc9f51fb5aae">
      <Text>A window. Bulletproof glass. A CLERK who has processed more bail payments than most people have had hot meals.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ef24427d-1c17-4443-a94d-6685ed7a0467">
      <Text>Jaz stands at the counter. The messenger bag open. Cash in stacks. She's counting it out her last bills. Hunter stands beside her.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="86e62c85-d0e9-4ca5-9f6a-61ca0bcee75e">
      <Text>She finishes. Steps back. Looks at the stacks. Her bag is empty.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="06a5b7ee-843b-42e2-b31e-fae2c02aad68">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="0e5dbfbc-f371-45c9-acce-5f52c2be0a78">
      <Text>(to the clerk)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="7c1e8c29-ea4e-4392-a2db-e107068c7ee8">
      <Text>$247,000. Um, I need a minute.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="1fb99ec5-1215-44cf-b52e-2fca54d8c3f5">
      <Text>BAIL CLERK</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="41e8f077-59da-4f6e-96ec-c91ded38e26a">
      <Text>Ma'am, the amount is two hundred fifty thousand—</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="5406d555-de52-4ecc-abb5-3c9bd6fde112">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="5bf89a0a-2b6b-4528-8b2d-87af1bfafbfe">
      <Text>I know what the amount is. I need a minute.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="56093c24-11f5-4a72-80e6-a206a38d51fe">
      <Text>Hunter looks at the cash. Looks at her. Does the math.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="cfcdd219-0362-4018-8b4b-579c1a11d304">
      <Text>He reaches into his pocket. Pulls out the wad of bills she tossed at him this morning. The clerk gives him a dirty look before starting to unwrinkled them.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a428d451-a688-44d4-9a22-a146259cecf3">
      <Text>She them in a neat stack on the counter next Jaz's.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="9e8eac08-1691-43da-994c-70e1576e729a">
      <Text>BaIL CLERK</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="c557a383-f3f9-489d-8d50-3113d30649c3">
      <Text>100- 250- 1000-</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="eba5b1ec-4011-45f7-bfac-d6a2b73e1bf4">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="8643b554-bdf7-4dfb-9c4a-be5d96d4131c">
      <Text>(looking at Jaz)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="cebef471-8530-4bea-99ff-2073b1326b47">
      <Text>Consider it a retainer adjustment.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="50de0df9-531e-47cd-bedd-7127f215c93b">
      <Text>baIL CLERK</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="ee272bcb-5a0b-4d63-b2c4-cc3018a3b44d">
      <Text>That's 3k, 250 thousand even, this one is yours.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="96dc4a02-8ab1-44f8-bb0b-d636e763e524">
      <Text>The clerk finishes the count, hands Hunter back a wrinkled C-note.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4401509f-6543-47c3-bba7-79d8643e5a3d">
      <Text>Jaz looks at the three thousand on the counter. Looks at Hunter. This man. This drunk, gambling, barely-licensed disaster in a wrinkled shirt.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="2440e50d-a717-4060-ad0b-17eb1571da1c">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="16b4d4b7-da9e-4a81-a78f-e4bd194f03bb">
      <Text>I'll pay you back.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="803e5c43-9c51-498a-9c76-40880716a277">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="6e59ed6f-288a-4860-9ed3-0b2844841c35">
      <Text>Consider it a 30% stake in your next poker night's winnings.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="d1b71c8e-c15d-4bf8-96f9-5675faf3a98d">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="49e88d35-5ef7-4826-a4c8-408631166966">
      <Text>(she chuckles warmly)</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="112b965d-67a1-4b9f-a6e1-b2086af9e71d">
      <Text>Deal.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6f38f14b-50af-4e91-99de-22cb75d006ea">
      <Text>She turns to the clerk. Pushes the cash forward. All of it. $250,000 even.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="0e93f94d-b1c2-4bb9-8af0-58db1f5e5e68">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="7aec54df-c0f2-4640-83e1-66e160aee53f">
      <Text>Two hundred fifty thousand. For Kevin McCort. Partially secured bond.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c5740889-ce7c-4054-bbe1-3eb7dd1df3ab">
      <Text>The clerk counts it. Stamps a form. Slides a receipt under the glass.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a669e40b-5509-40ec-9349-28b1b472ee0a">
      <Text>Jaz takes the receipt. Folds it. Puts it in the messenger bag.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8c8d8aab-2087-4181-90d2-bc62d2071b8d">
      <Text>She's broke.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="54985ca4-fa5e-46d8-ba6f-3e807f578877">
      <Text>Her family is free, for the moment.</Text>
      <UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" id="5f6c73a4-bf4e-44e3-98ae-5f93e8ca46c8">
      <SceneProperties Length="12 5/8" Page="47" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HUNTER">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JANET">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JAZ">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEVIN">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WAITRESS">
            <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" OutlineLevel="0" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
          </CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. DINER - LOWER MANHATTAN - NIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="5cc36014-903c-4f13-b89b-2a02f8e700f4">
      <Text>The kind of diner that exists on every block south of Canal and north of nowhere. Laminated menus. A waitress who calls everyone "hon." A booth by the window with a view of a parking garage.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="898b77a6-3182-423a-910e-1ab65698233f">
      <Text>JANET, JAMIE, and JAZ sit in the booth. They have been here for three hours. The food arrived two hours and forty-five minutes ago.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8720b8db-bc33-44a4-a137-c280cb4db609">
      <Text>Nobody is eating.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="19a9b6c0-2d8d-44bc-b59f-b33a4809707f">
      <Text>Janet has a bowl of yogurt parfait. The granola has gone soft. She holds a spoon. It has not moved in twenty minutes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="da0d0f23-f600-43fe-b610-66337f06f329">
      <Text>She is back in the Lululemon— it's what she was arrested in, it's what she has. Over it, draped across her shoulders: Hunter's jacket. Under the table, below the hem of the Lululemon, her left ankle. A light blinks. Nobody has looked at it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b6245635-4e74-42e1-acf5-bca7e564add7">
      <Text>Jamie has a mountain of chocolate chip pancakes. Whipped cream on top— but the cream has broken, gone grainy and translucent.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="46333247-3f52-4f19-8a19-c3912fad5b6a">
      <Text>Jaz has fries. She's arranging them into patterns and then destroying the patterns.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9488f4e6-dc71-4a93-92b5-a692737c83f6">
      <Text>They are a family at a diner. They look like a stock photo that went wrong.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="df9a25d3-52c2-4f40-bfb5-bc125b503b2f">
      <Text>The door opens.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="561104df-ac42-4a7c-8e4a-39015657eb43">
      <Text>HUNTER walks in first. Holding the door. Under one arm: the yellow legal pad. In the other hand: the brown paper bag. Behind him: KEVIN.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b03fe987-cc75-4e62-a352-e3a7f25b002d">
      <Text>Kevin McCort. Ink still on his fingers, faded now to gray-blue. An ANKLE MONITOR bulging under his left pant leg— black, chunky, the size of a deck of cards. He's trying to walk like it isn't there. It is absolutely there.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="64f7e27c-1acf-40b4-909b-806b56f6ce47">
      <Text>Jaz sees him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="e72b622f-6fc9-4d53-9052-a2e9d6b95857">
      <Text>She's out of the booth before he's three steps inside. Across the diner. Arms around him. Hard.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c5aad7f4-d8cd-4f5c-ad42-4f5a8ccfe6fc">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="d4778901-99b8-4afd-b09a-2a75ec6c1124">
      <Text>(into his chest)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="cc4b8a00-c309-4bf6-a64d-5311a02db34a">
      <Text>Dad.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8bdd0ce0-0511-49db-9743-42ae581c24b2">
      <Text>Kevin stands there. His arms come up slowly— not because he doesn't want to hold her, but because the last time he hugged his daughter she had hair on both sides of her head and was wearing a custom Princeton hoodie from J.Crew.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8f66cb3d-31cb-41d9-92e1-3fad893442c3">
      <Text>His hand lands on the shaved side of her skull. He feels it. The stubble. The tattoo under his palm. He doesn't pull away.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a35abaa8-3f6a-46ce-b44e-3580e9ae490c">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="d4a25f4c-2f33-4689-a29a-fc6a468449d2">
      <Text>(rough, quiet)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="6a046a25-97ab-4cfb-a519-e2f06d965413">
      <Text>Hey, kid.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9a6ddf73-3424-4c82-b5ec-e79608b44fe3">
      <Text>She pulls back. Turns to Hunter. Hugs him too. Shorter. But real.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="e9aad459-2342-46c6-a3b8-593b71f582fa">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="5b3e817d-d48b-4d73-b52e-6d171d93985b">
      <Text>(stiffening)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="900fd20c-1bec-48a0-a090-fdb2aed20554">
      <Text>Okay. That's— yeah. Okay.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f7c4468f-4446-46ac-b428-a5aec7ab1ca2">
      <Text>Kevin slides into the booth next to Janet. She looks at him. He looks at her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="2ffd49b1-3c88-4d59-ab6a-1821ac413d72">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="4eb606d2-3231-4164-a8df-601e752b6b72">
      <Text>You have ink on your forehead.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="6226488d-4291-46ac-bef3-5557653fec29">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="cc552f60-fc7f-45f8-8b74-c688295f2658">
      <Text>I know.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="835e8d22-435b-4b01-83e2-bf9ffc637138">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="ce0e12a0-38e2-4a34-817b-c3c26a38c522">
      <Text>It's been there all day?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="8d44835f-4c4b-45f6-9b8d-b86052bc7f37">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="d11d5a61-4ed4-4eb3-bf62-6793c445f372">
      <Text>Apparently.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="16fc99fa-a14b-4e78-a168-945307a41733">
      <Text>She licks her thumb. Reaches across. Wipes his forehead. It doesn't come off, but she tries.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b6d530fb-fcd4-4b3b-be8a-476987be98cc">
      <Text>Hunter pulls a chair to the end of the booth. Sits. Sets the brown bag on the floor between his feet.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="0bf34136-c0f0-47f4-90fc-b36277f5d0c1">
      <Text>The waitress approaches.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ec369db4-d797-431f-9710-5fb0b03bf3ac">
      <Text>WAITRESS</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="d62192df-af33-4b0b-94f9-ec418ab21420">
      <Text>Can I get you two anything, hon?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4f767061-31a9-4955-b244-8c91cbe1ebb4">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="dcbee254-3fef-479e-88f3-b50eb6f60b88">
      <Text>Coffee. Black.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="2907e65e-da66-453a-86f3-a065ec1ed217">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="77d5ca8c-1ae6-4e1c-a3a9-f1f1ad7cdce4">
      <Text>(not looking up)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="c4d85866-37be-4765-adac-d665b7b6ee2d">
      <Text>Glass of ice. Just the ice. Thanks.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="68fb2135-66b3-4a73-89d3-adab5e7368d0">
      <Text>Kevin looks at the table. At his family. At the diner. He takes a breath. The Big Daddy breath. The COO breath. Something in the room relaxes slightly, reflexively, at the sound of it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="03dce624-cfe2-4ee3-9258-4a0a23db4d5f">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="ef8a8c00-1713-4f4c-bf2f-001f08c4368a">
      <Text>Okay. Let's figure out what we have. We go to the Hamptons tonight, regroup. We'll walk through the whole thing from the beginning, get ahead of this—</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a21e9625-d315-45ed-aaf4-0fe3c3e29099">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="b9013057-42b9-4199-b491-bb49dd9cd92f">
      <Text>(without looking up)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="90349ee6-357b-4481-b992-5017ee29b026">
      <Text>We won't.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="8a49ad29-aed3-4faa-bb09-98814b5e8f5a">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="5049b29a-ba20-4197-b84b-9a1cb61685ee">
      <Text>What?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="45115f6d-ac31-46fc-b93b-e509dc2d7b1a">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="e80d08b2-3798-4df3-9870-315bfac469f8">
      <Text>The Hamptons property is seized as are the cars that would get you there.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="8c626eb4-e5d5-4574-8fc5-11d8415968af">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="fd8c22a6-b860-4cf3-ae99-073e903ef21d">
      <Text>Fine. The Waldorf. I know the manager. We get a suite, we sit down, we have an acc—</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="58f853fa-7314-4d6d-915f-022d73ac9774">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="72c16a13-e31f-4184-a56c-a9581e40cfd1">
      <Text>That is an MedAnalytics account, not yours.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="fe3c249f-8a79-4ab5-995a-b3c44422ee57">
      <Text>(Sets down the pen. Looks at Kevin.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a1b65151-0ad4-48d1-b977-9e2782aefc40">
      <Text>Kevin. You can't go to the Hamptons. You can't go to the Waldorf. You can't go anywhere that isn't on THE approved list of your conditional release- that I just spent two hours negotiating. That thing on your leg is a GPS unit tethered to a monitoring dashboard, and any deviation from the approved property confinement location generates an automatic alert before you've gone fifty feet.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="bf69cd5d-b631-484c-a8c7-67d37a382d71">
      <Text>Kevin stares at the ankle monitor.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="cbf9ef76-ac08-4241-8917-5cfbdc3acf81">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="d8eab837-9cf7-45ac-be0a-bba35e63c551">
      <Text>What are the approved locations?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="9914e346-2cc7-43dc-98eb-b7c6dcbb2ed0">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="271f6e70-3ed0-495a-af34-ba18b8fcede0">
      <Text>I'll get to that. First I need you to be clear about your situation, and I need you to do the thing we talked about. Shut the fuck up- and listen to me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="9de4e85b-734d-4afa-aa04-324305aa42c6">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="d9507103-eae3-417a-a3cc-fc1b669b8565">
      <Text>(wary)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="cf49804b-aaf3-4240-bf85-3fc3ed2380f8">
      <Text>Go ahead.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c6b6e5ba-439c-4cd9-93bf-2381f7be6d7b">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="26e380e8-1985-4c38-8523-c8594fbb024b">
      <Text>Janet needs her own lawyer.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="70bf21bb-51dd-4a44-889f-4ce7e07acf3f">
      <Text>The table goes quiet in a particular way.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="47111784-2ccc-4703-8f64-4238b5e42e61">
      <Text>Janet looks up from the yogurt parfait. She has the expression of someone who has been waiting to end up abandoned for her whole life.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="8c9c5750-9a10-4f85-9a92-a8f553c12bc4">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="b96a2b98-4aed-400b-b64c-9f55b15aa856">
      <Text>(directly to Hunter)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="5fdde97a-a8bb-4447-8d16-6da98d921f76">
      <Text>Can't you—</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="654ee99a-a896-4b4e-b420-b4a341ce4291">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="2d007468-a38a-47b7-bd76-efe177cded3e">
      <Text>No.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c0c41fc0-4476-460f-92c2-5c81997f6b61">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="4b73378e-552f-4bef-b722-b0c805582619">
      <Text>I'm asking if you can represent—</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="56e0bdca-08b6-47bd-8dd8-11be94a329b1">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="d4610e41-5db8-4ca3-8776-d58874537b3b">
      <Text>I can't. I'm sorry. I genuinely cannot.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="58470e40-3bbd-4611-b61a-bd305d646b21">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="1b3edbfd-5e6f-472d-895b-7bb3fb1eb91d">
      <Text>(a beat, recalibrating)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="ffd94397-1e6a-4f18-bd18-db0a69bbe68d">
      <Text>can't or won't?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="039bfda7-480d-4510-9bc1-6cdb7ca95487">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="1598c4ee-f8f1-4c0f-9854-299ec7623a77">
      <Text>(softens, his heart visibly breaking yet another crack)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="30219a54-1de7-4a04-8bd3-b13bc52d2384">
      <Text>Can't. KEVIN is my client of record. You are a co-defendant. Those two things cannot share a lawyer. Your interests and Kevin's interests may look identical right now, but the DA charged YOU separately and specifically, which means the law treats them as potentially adverse. If I represent both of you- I have a conflict of interest that ends my ability to represent either of you, and could be disbarred for trying. I cannot give you legal advice.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="de5d4947-d901-413e-962b-7b40fdad6176">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="d0988880-659e-4ed8-b4c0-3bd76898c571">
      <Text>(quietly)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="f1025919-8cf5-48df-8067-d95a3c49af8e">
      <Text>What does that mean. "Potentially adverse."</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4b7d047a-5c28-41dd-83c3-dea162c69e7a">
      <Text>Hunter takes a deep breath, looks out the window, up at the ceiling, taps his fingers against the table waiting for the universe to generate a distraction that means he does not have to answer- the universe does not. Fuck. He makes direct intentional contact with Jaz.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="e5324a07-fb22-4c27-8513-48ace8a6e82e">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="da8f2f68-d0d7-4c78-9701-fa24817dcd81">
      <Text>Jaz, good question and thank YOU for asking. It means the DA charged your mom with conspiracy to create a pressure point. To give her an exit. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="bcaca3cc-4877-472d-8ce5-53d2d923a90d">
      <Text>(holding Jaz's gaze)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="da8f2f68-d0d7-4c78-9701-fa24817dcd81">
      <Text>Your mom's attorney's job is to evaluate what that exit looks like and advise her on whether to take it. My job is to make sure that whatever conversation happens, Kevin is protected from the outcome of it. One lawyer cannot do both of those jobs.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="aa32a64e-da49-431e-a329-847df6888dc2">
      <Text>Janet absorbs this. The spoon is still in her hand.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="d1ff6638-2b66-458f-a11c-ab53a1a1797a">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="67d4e3e7-84c3-4a77-8738-9449d88ded80">
      <Text>So I need a lawyer I don't have. Who I can't afford. To tell me what my options are in a situation I don't—</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="55e847b4-eda0-43d1-9adc-61abc48f5702">
      <Text>She stops. Starts again.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="51c8544b-aeae-419e-9630-5235e34ce8ba">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="cc1a2ced-2525-4e33-aa70-66e53b7f0be5">
      <Text>I don't know what a conspiracy charge means. I don't know what I'm supposed to do or say or—</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="88aa814b-b4f0-4d25-bc14-1cb626f99ce6">
      <Text>She looks at Hunter. The mask is still on— it will always be mostly on— but underneath it something is working very hard.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="e2503ef4-9f30-4c71-b5fd-2c42ae0f47e0">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="042f048c-5536-4a8d-8b60-f6934b628305">
      <Text>I don't know what questions to ask.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3f650a25-730b-41c0-ab07-8d7d95e4989e">
      <Text>Hunter looks at her. There is a version of this moment where he tells her exactly what she needs to know, walks her through the whole architecture, because she's sitting across from him and she's frightened in a way she's managing beautifully and it would be so easy to just answer the question.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="604aea2f-3ab7-4c6f-99d3-f0fd0fcf544c">
      <Text>He can't. And she can see he can't.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="efd1a25b-d825-4064-aabf-cf93a8584973">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="41a40302-09fc-4f4f-a0ca-9a55233fd577">
      <Text>(carefully)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="87a84006-59c4-429c-a528-cbaca1bb7f5b">
      <Text>I can tell you that you need a lawyer before you talk to anyone about anything. Anyone at all.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="00711352-79f6-451e-a44c-eed33d9426b7">
      <Text>He holds her gaze for one beat longer than necessary. That's all he can give her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6ce82582-fd61-4140-b520-74936519baa2">
      <Text>She nods once. Files it. Her face closes again.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4c3871a7-9dfc-448c-a531-344df763bf60">
      <Text>Kevin has been watching this. His brain running at full speed, processing the terrain, mapping the problem, identifying the resource gaps, beginning to formulate— </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="06059d0d-052f-4dc4-b71a-23b7d74175ef">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="e6e133fe-ee83-4072-97d0-c19f05b95e5a">
      <Text>Okay. I sit down with Hunter and we align on the narrative. We get our story straight so that when Janet's attorney comes in they're working from—</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c6267f69-4df9-4582-bdea-0ab0b186055e">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="82295122-9130-4a5c-85bc-a07744781511">
      <Text>Kevin.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="d202f34b-deb8-4147-948c-c2dcd0f82433">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="775b7a60-98f1-4941-a0ab-35b418dd50a5">
      <Text>—the same framework we're operating from, and Janet's interests are protected because we've already established what the—</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="1da81fe5-ee23-494b-88da-cabcc2044f15">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="1282017c-a096-447c-b8c1-23937aa87519">
      <Text>(fist slams on the table rattling the dishes)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="b483e152-4dfa-4e50-bbe9-dc41c359ffa1">
      <Text>Kevin. Stop.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ed7e4da9-2bf2-458e-b82b-0715f898168f">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="fbe63494-2a5f-4fdc-9b02-492bb21e0125">
      <Text>I'm not asking her to say anything. I'm asking you and me to—</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ec34534a-ea0e-42ac-905e-0380e9bb9de9">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="88d8f029-f302-4a76-b8ca-f56b6df68718">
      <Text>You need to stop talking right now.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="65f23a56-8e0a-4ef5-b1f1-3fd2e21c951a">
      <Text>The force of it lands. Kevin stops.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="79b433b7-3012-4b5b-9fd7-2418b39fe9bb">
      <Text>Hunter's voice hasn't risen. It's quieter, actually. Which is worse.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4c27294c-bbbb-4642-80a0-a0f5fca8c8af">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="f0d54827-7cf3-4fa9-ab22-d294fffc9bed">
      <Text>You cannot discuss the case with Janet. You cannot discuss her defense with her. You cannot share strategy with her, you cannot suggest strategy to her, you cannot ask her questions about what she knows or what she said or what happened, and you cannot tell her what to say to her lawyer when she gets one.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="0a59eab2-057e-4268-bbff-3def0bf4e1e7">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="1f6ed221-323a-490a-b3f6-b257c44e4fdd">
      <Text>We're married—</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="0e2db1d3-1446-456a-8a59-6854501a15eb">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="a10f0e01-7324-48c5-91e5-e22287806260">
      <Text>That's not a legal defense for violating a co-defendant contact order. If you give her legal advice about this case— if you say anything she could use in her defense that came from you— you are in contempt. I will have the added bonus of being your lawyer handling a contempt issue on top of a securities fraud case. And you both go back to a cell while the hearing is scheduled. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="0a16c83f-87eb-4f0f-8a5c-988de2f96193">
      <Text>(the sound of Janets spoon dropping hard against the table)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="a10f0e01-7324-48c5-91e5-e22287806260">
      <Text>And if I am in the room and her attorney is not- I am your counsel of record, present, and not stopping it. That crosses me into pretrial release condition violation into potential obstruction or witness tampering.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="903a22ee-e2a8-4687-889d-2f5ecbd5c962">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="3976a2f1-81cf-4a6d-a571-d89ac5702c29">
      <Text>(very still)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="8c841d36-ea2c-4f46-a140-52648ca9025b">
      <Text>She goes back to a cell.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="e60b7e38-4eb9-4843-85d6-945a8673e28f">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="2bd896d4-6a2d-49db-ba05-c4421a63df92">
      <Text>Yes, you both do. And I get disbarred.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="3a79a8d3-8f25-4a05-868d-7c5557938a6f">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="4c49124d-bc71-4df0-8d0a-9f176eb4156d">
      <Text>For me talking to my wife.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4eabc411-4a06-49cf-984e-6b397e1b0be8">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="93a38527-8178-44d6-8d3c-4c08afdee3c7">
      <Text>For discussing the case with your co-defendant without both of your attorneys. Yes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="0c894f16-e94d-4329-9230-b6f19fc453a6">
      <Text>The table is silent. The diner moves around them—  Kevin looks at Janet. Janet looks back at him. Twenty-two years of a shared life and there has never been a wall in this specific place. There have been walls— Kevin knows that, somewhere underneath all the things he has failed to look at he knows that— but not this one.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="106e0ed1-088e-47e0-a33c-f1bef7b37fbe">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="5c3e7dde-faa2-4c14-a00e-67fae0eb5a0b">
      <Text>(cautious)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="5572fa8e-04f6-4306-9982-2c68385b79d3">
      <Text>Can I ask her if she has a court date.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="622bf69a-21f0-464e-a1b8-6104f92d536a">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="bf327010-abe9-4fba-83ee-97a628bad144">
      <Text>No.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="1f1e414d-5c39-4be6-818b-c17c7d249dde">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="2d572f91-55f3-4377-981b-1cb6bddb41d4">
      <Text>Can I ask if she has a meeting with her lawyer.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="b24fe848-7ca7-4022-8218-c89c33c81f0d">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="fe8a59b1-015d-499e-b65f-2eca70bd4ebd">
      <Text>No.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c584641c-35fb-4840-9bd3-ce3a4b7b0dfa">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="d62880ff-3fa6-4bf9-a6a4-7f1772ac6f21">
      <Text>Can I—</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="78db0dde-405f-44f9-a039-c48fc50f725e">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="53c6527b-d69e-4e54-af86-4b1861290138">
      <Text>If it touches the case, the charges, legal proceedings, attorneys, anything adjacent to any of that, anyone involved in the case in any way— no. You cannot ask. She cannot answer. That's the order.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="75bea07a-6700-476d-959b-e27eac23a8d4">
      <Text>Kevin looks at his wife. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="4b9dd86c-0b37-48df-befa-14ba8ad3bf3f">
      <Text>He has no tools for this. Every tool Kevin McCort has ever used— his network, his position, his ability to convene a room and move it toward a solution— is gone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="72acc94b-292a-497c-bcc1-15c7d642f518">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="f8dbf1d8-501d-4dcb-ac9d-839dc43549b1">
      <Text>(to the table, barely audible)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="ed369c75-a0c3-4f16-8c8c-d15d3db958fd">
      <Text>So what can we talk about.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="0c90c10a-2239-4e41-a8b8-9eaaa147e31d">
      <Text>A long beat.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="02c60fb3-68be-481a-bf91-8fd8c410f9c7">
      <Text>JANET</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="1db7f861-dd34-4185-9ae3-c64ec5e8892f">
      <Text>(looking at his forehead)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="12e330a6-b006-465e-b0ed-793882e8547b">
      <Text>Your ink- and your daughter's ink.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="1e7be69f-b9e9-4157-8a1e-15c423035aaa">
      <Text>It lands somewhere between funny and devastating. Kevin doesn't laugh. But something in his face does something.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a9d0122f-88cf-4d72-9b6b-a1ecdf3cdb42">
      <Text>The waitress returns. Sets down Kevin's coffee. Sets down a glass of ice in front of Hunter. Just ice.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c7d3ca50-a122-4447-bf53-8480483b3368">
      <Text>Hunter reaches down. Lifts the brown bag. Pulls out a fifth of JAMESON— new bottle, tax seal intact. Sets it next to the glass.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="69663f1e-1de6-4494-b182-02359e15f750">
      <Text>He breaks the seal. Three fingers over ice. Slides the glass across to Kevin.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a93fe986-61e3-4eb7-b97f-c0e154cbd40e">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="6f21d484-989b-4872-8676-0a4e8cbec176">
      <Text>I didn't—</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="1b978802-53d7-4275-bd7c-76f09d56975a">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="0345c65c-a649-4b04-a7be-f4b5941c97c5">
      <Text>You look like you need it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="eb3ce54c-f5a9-4568-b1b2-a243f2e88d71">
      <Text>Kevin picks it up. Hunter tips the bottle back. A long, straight, unapologetic pull, drains a full third of the bottle without flinching. Sets it down. Wipes his mouth.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="adfac6da-4d33-4fc9-955a-293a68cc0fa7">
      <Text>Jamie watches this. Cataloguing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="bb12bae6-1619-458e-8df6-f2f2b06ed73e">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="daa8e9b3-0685-4c42-836c-2b2d479c1f85">
      <Text>Devices.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="17ada0bc-baeb-4716-9b81-2b3184c8d0c9">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="4e0e9a98-4073-4214-95bc-6b85c211c4ba">
      <Text>What about them.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="cf854830-6a35-445c-aa70-854ded33f84d">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="caa7ec55-0d21-40a5-a408-66274a045c89">
      <Text>Your phones were seized. Both of yours, and Jamie's because he's a minor and it was in the house. When- if you get new ones— and you'll need to, there's a pre-disclosure 36 hour window— you report them in advance to your pretrial services officer. His name is Dennis Pruitt. Sussex County. Every device either of you touch is required to be reported. No encrypted messaging applications. No disappearing messages. Anything Pruitt finds that wasn't disclosed is a violation.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a2ea4f0a-25b1-4092-97f0-f4e2a62c516c">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="27f53583-26b3-4bf3-847d-81e86ce57b3d">
      <Text>(very flat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="c2596212-a090-4522-975e-0cd38b16db1a">
      <Text>So whoever this guys is gets the password to any phone I touch.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4b1a480a-487c-4451-8b9d-828ae1822f60">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="8729bb0d-08ec-4d64-a0cb-cf5d81c653d4">
      <Text>Your pretrial service officer, Yes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="f3f039ee-c8f9-478a-828b-13d2db407b26">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="b02a44ef-7118-4690-bc25-5e4bfd87394f">
      <Text>And reads my messages.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="438ecabf-7437-4007-882f-46f4e41059ce">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="91782110-b452-4fea-9765-df46bddc6e85">
      <Text>Can. On request, at his whim, no probable cause. Yes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="9a65cc9f-8032-4695-85b4-733ebea7cfaa">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="7e5dc469-b7aa-4ea1-a05d-c04151cbc92c">
      <Text>(completing the geometry)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="fa83401a-d1e9-4a38-bf3f-67fc51d1cc31">
      <Text>So I can't communicate with my wife of 22 years about the case. I can't call my former lawyers because they all work for the company. I can't contact anyone at or at all involved with MedAnalytic. I can't go anywhere that isn't on your approved list. I can't—</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="05865af7-5d56-41f2-9d86-30c55e617fd2">
      <Text>He stops. Runs it again.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="645868cf-3cba-4df6-a064-d322e4b8637a">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="93593887-2c2c-42dd-8375-c4041e51b216">
      <Text>I can't do anything.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="0dac348c-9f74-48fb-9f28-8b2c938d36be">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="56971dca-e4a2-4908-9973-23d6d6a442bf">
      <Text>That is an accurate summary of your immediate situation. Yes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="d99d6bde-ce38-4b64-a450-85d3ec4b6b4f">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="5b381c60-56d1-4aea-b725-5ef27c82231c">
      <Text>And you. You're what I have. Columbia Law, bottom third, a burner phone that is out of minutes... and a bottle of Jameson in a diner booth— and what?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="033974b3-686e-436f-84ad-22bc7f01bf04">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="4cb14a23-048e-43df-93e7-87ba81be76ca">
      <Text>I have Sixty eight bucks-</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="4d680aaf-0b3c-49eb-9843-9e4a5833a424">
      <Text>(puling the last of it out and two coins)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="4cb14a23-048e-43df-93e7-87ba81be76ca">
      <Text>And thirty cents. And a current New State bar card.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c62c999e-af06-4990-a0e1-ee21a5cce9cb">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="093e2c24-57ff-4a29-baac-2f62fd863f1b">
      <Text>—and this is— this is the hand.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="9fa72384-d7e8-4418-81f7-765b011dbdd3">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="16138bc3-caef-4071-91b9-9d0197fa7318">
      <Text>That's the hand.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="35fc94f1-c9ab-4362-87d5-dfb3d9ab28e2">
      <Text>Kevin looks at him. At the Jameson. At the ankle monitor pulsing green below the table. His gaze moves to Janet. The Lululemon. Hunter's jacket over her shoulders.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d2759fca-3d18-4abd-a091-fbf8b7b4feb8">
      <Text>And then he sees it. Her ankle monitor.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d2759fca-3d18-4abd-a091-fbf8b7b4feb8">
      <Text>It is the one thing in Janet McCort's life that she cannot make look like it belongs. Cannot make elegant. Cannot integrate. It sits on her ankle like a rebuke from the physical world.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9022f238-daae-4081-8a9a-9f7ad086a452">
      <Text>She feels him see it. Her chin comes up a fraction. Her face gives him nothing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="75b2f1db-a879-4e3c-afec-14e16417c1d8">
      <Text>Kevin looks at his wife— really looks at her, the way he has failed to look at her for twenty-two years— and sees, for the first time, that she is completely alone. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b7ee21bf-2995-45a2-b2f8-57ae6dea9490">
      <Text>And for the first time in his life he is completely impotent.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d4fbef61-3563-4145-9be7-1eaecbf501a5">
      <Text>He opens his mouth.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f6294b63-af68-4d84-85a6-aa2a6e032c89">
      <Text>Hunter's hand comes down flat on the table between them. Not loud. Just final.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="ba3a1eb3-c39d-4c2c-9377-20667e1996a7">
      <Text>Kevin closes his mouth.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="cc9ec8b6-9dd9-4c46-b167-32868702c13a">
      <Text>The gap between them— eighteen inches of diner booth— is suddenly the largest distance in the room.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3476b724-68d1-445f-b2c9-0766465160fb">
      <Text>They are all very quiet-</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3476b724-68d1-445f-b2c9-0766465160fb">
      <Text>Then-</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="3ab31393-4744-46c9-9f07-01ff273cf422">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="0742ca4f-0b2a-4cbd-8b6c-4ae4ae27ed31">
      <Text>(back to Hunter)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="9bd812ba-83be-4d1d-97a4-d422129d6fd1">
      <Text>The cash bail. You have sixty eight dollars.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="365fb446-4f3e-4df3-accf-cb406f6d4f3e">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="712e31d0-3452-4b77-9cd1-f9aa010ff3fa">
      <Text>And thirty cents. Yes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="9fe1b76f-7e5a-4abf-aef1-94681b77e7a4">
      <Text>Kevin looks down the booth. Past Janet. Past Jamie and his collapsed pancakes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="3ecf81f8-80a2-4eb6-ac0b-82757f2daa31">
      <Text>To Jaz.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d726be33-9316-4579-b1c6-02df529e884c">
      <Text>Ramones shirt. Combat boots tucked under her ass. Exhausted. Broke. But with the unquenchable fire burning bright behind her eyes that she is no longer bothering to mask.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="7d6bf6cf-6949-4e91-b09c-0f1ef594bc6e">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="2ce3f18e-9ba3-43b7-9709-1c65373251f2">
      <Text>(barely)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="5b2a85c3-0bf0-4db5-8515-7bdd31c7f73a">
      <Text>You bailed us out.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="2ff98af5-3b68-4b1b-9fee-02d3bde7ccb0">
      <Text>(Hunter clears his throat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="a0c785ed-5760-4dc2-a04f-01d79242cf15">
      <Text>ME. Out.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="7046a72f-5000-4207-afc5-42a27a58f618">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="a4e54612-6a11-4fc6-b11b-a6c57c52055b">
      <Text>Yes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="5124603c-af6a-4f38-81b2-57525ef91f49">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="1d0a5d95-e5ed-4073-9e64-f9715d49b18b">
      <Text>How?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="dfe967d8-fc92-426c-bb7d-2d4fd9fa8d83">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="5dd04563-5d58-402c-984c-4b18a3a89185">
      <Text>Poker.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="6cf15e10-c867-48bd-a58a-5cc75a8d7c16">
      <Text>He opens his mouth. Stops. The universe has shifted in a very disorienting way and his usual vocabulary doesn't work in it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="6c7bcc0d-02e9-49f3-94f3-870c1e6532f0">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="3b5ee7d7-6dab-455d-b44e-4f8fda8eaee7">
      <Text>(to Hunter)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b1b73dce-d669-4275-a764-18d64439d48d">
      <Text>How much?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="8999d42b-c2e7-4927-b70b-b9d35a4ff234">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="57d27194-9366-4dcc-9466-276278b814aa">
      <Text>YOUR bail was two hundred and fifty thou—</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="c2b4ae06-5920-4840-91c9-c64571c8b569">
      <Text>Kevin holds up his palm. He needs a second.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="3d567fcc-c149-4617-aaab-2a16548e8acd">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="6a58e2ce-1f15-4b55-b823-845634daafbc">
      <Text>When did you play poker?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="d3c47735-71f4-4fb5-81fb-998fe8b94a1f">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="8066f50f-175d-42f6-804a-74aef8e69ef5">
      <Text>Last night.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="dfe501fa-bc8f-409a-8f37-6fae3a159f0d">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="d419922d-5a11-49a4-8adf-b7d25a316fea">
      <Text>For more than a quarter of a million dollars.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ef02fd45-6ff2-4a2b-911f-1315216e8347">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="3b769b92-f802-481f-ba5f-5f9a490bc9b8">
      <Text>The cash portion of the pot was north of that, yes. And now between the two of you I'm cleared out. Not even the next buy-in.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a3435471-febf-4f13-ab76-68906bd1747f">
      <Text>She pulls the manila folder. Sets it on the table.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="08c6dd9d-0143-41d3-9248-121dd96a8369">
      <Text>Kevin opens it. Reads. Fast, precise. Reads the deed, the transfer docs, the debt agreements all, appraisals, filed, all professional. signed, sealed, delivered Whitfield, Park &amp; </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1">Liang</Text>
      <Text> letterhead, partner signatures. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="4d1f570c-e7c9-4327-bd29-6669491d1a85">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="2213728f-621b-4b16-ad3a-0a5afcf218c7">
      <Text>This is real?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="ddb5521d-2476-443b-b7c2-40be9d265557">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="2d55ffb2-7f17-4eb6-9e69-13d3532cd539">
      <Text>Plus twelve million in liens.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c985909d-6a26-4a91-a4c5-e5b1446aee33">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="adb7b171-2a2e-47d4-8117-2a75b08b4792">
      <Text>To whom?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="a87fc381-4d59-4c94-bf1a-e6648c11de71">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="a6f0b0e3-8240-4f3a-bb23-e34207a39c1a">
      <Text>Me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d4aeaf71-c427-4ae6-8af1-96990f6188b8">
      <Text>Kevin pulls out the vintage pamphlet from 1975. Looks at the pool, the lobby, the grand staircase. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d4aeaf71-c427-4ae6-8af1-96990f6188b8">
      <Text>Then-</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d4aeaf71-c427-4ae6-8af1-96990f6188b8">
      <Text>He looks at Phoenix. Really looks. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="d4aeaf71-c427-4ae6-8af1-96990f6188b8">
      <Text>He has seen that look across boardroom tables his entire career— sees the eyes of someone who understands how to walk out of any room with the thing they want. The killer. The closer. He has never once seen it on his daughter's face.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="f24c3da1-2a94-4d48-bd9e-bd28ead18bc7">
      <Text>He's never looked the way he is now.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="76d49508-2ef3-49ae-92de-50d71d80558e">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="e45b345d-35c0-4cb3-9e4f-695e1e6b9623">
      <Text>What did you put on the table for this.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="b7c66903-d972-4611-9144-e49e73c5a30e">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="02ff1b35-4c3c-4441-b1fa-bed68ab56c67">
      <Text>(completely natural)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="b804d526-ce75-47ba-81c9-a022c02762fa">
      <Text>Whatever it took.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="8cd33ee9-afb5-4516-a3d0-1230fb51bb4d">
      <Text>Kevin looks at Janet. Janet looks at Kevin. Jamie looks at the pancakes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="a6ca2a5f-2a9b-44f0-ad04-44aed6978dc6">
      <Text>A long silence.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c64349bd-fc55-450e-bffe-afe77d6a38c4">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="4f02b488-fb6e-489b-be5d-ba5ce8cf15b0">
      <Text>Ok- ok- </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="52d865dd-28bc-4433-a613-88c327c777e3">
      <Text>(almost defeated)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="4f02b488-fb6e-489b-be5d-ba5ce8cf15b0">
      <Text>How do we get there?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="46382854-db31-4044-ab5f-8177837ee46d">
      <Text>HUNTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="1aca9f5e-4578-47d7-a3b6-0d722355ab6a">
      <Text>I have access to a car. It starts most of the time.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="b0eac395-63bc-4b22-929d-984cf925ab2a">
      <Text>Kevin picks up the deed again. Looks at the pamphlet photo.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action" id="dc3c1fa5-0c0a-447e-aff3-ae4a9736c3c2">
      <Text>He wants to say something. There is nothing left that he is allowed to say.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="3880ab08-bf94-4add-a67d-8799c7e94cb5">
      <Text>KEVIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" id="5241dc13-74cf-4d40-9a6f-d01bac146bf4">
      <Text>(quiet)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue" id="3de3560c-62f0-4f27-b849-cb9018434624">
      <Text>The Playboy.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character" id="c7f6934e-0aca-4d36-99e1-09e419f87aa5">
      <Text>JAZ</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="2.50" RightIndent="6.00" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No" Type="Dialogue" id="d13a9c37-c958-4673-bcdb-f6e74f8f08aa">
      <Text>The Playboy.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition" id="a6a13cbd-0983-449d-9eac-209771ebd7df">
      <Text>SMASH TO BLACK.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
  </Content>

